WEBVTT

00:03.090 --> 00:05.962
[Suspenseful music]

00:06.006 --> 00:12.490
♪

00:12.534 --> 00:15.537
[wind whistling]

00:24.372 --> 00:27.331
[breathing heavily]

00:27.375 --> 00:34.382
♪

00:38.429 --> 00:40.083
[grunts]

00:40.127 --> 00:45.523
♪

00:45.567 --> 00:47.308
[steam hissing]

00:47.351 --> 00:49.266
[engine clanging]

00:49.310 --> 00:51.268
[grunts]

00:51.312 --> 00:52.530
[metal squeaking]

00:52.574 --> 00:54.097
Hey, you need to tell
your sister

00:54.141 --> 00:55.707
to slow the hell down!

00:55.751 --> 00:58.188
The engine isn't gonna
take this much longer!

00:58.232 --> 01:00.103
You know Gwenn
doesn't listen to me!

01:00.147 --> 01:02.149
♪

01:02.192 --> 01:03.541
Yeah?
Well, she sure as hell

01:03.585 --> 01:06.196
doesn't listen to us either.

01:06.240 --> 01:08.590
Dana, it's no joke!
She needs to slow down!

01:08.633 --> 01:10.287
I'll let her know!

01:10.331 --> 01:14.639
♪

01:14.683 --> 01:18.339
[ominous rumbling]

01:19.253 --> 01:21.255
Gwenn, you need to ease off.

01:21.298 --> 01:22.647
This goddamn engine isn't...

01:22.691 --> 01:26.477
♪

01:26.521 --> 01:28.566
They're not getting away
from us this time.

01:28.610 --> 01:29.698
Here.

01:29.741 --> 01:32.135
It's, uh... it's ready.

01:32.179 --> 01:33.354
You only got one shot
at this, okay?

01:33.397 --> 01:35.138
So make it count.

01:35.182 --> 01:37.358
You're sure this
tracking device contraption

01:37.401 --> 01:39.490
of yours, it's... it's gonna
grab on to their ship?

01:39.534 --> 01:41.144
It should.

01:41.188 --> 01:42.754
I think.
Hey, we're gonna lose them

01:42.798 --> 01:46.149
in the fog if the two of you
don't hurry up.

01:46.193 --> 01:48.151
[Stammers]

01:48.195 --> 01:55.158
♪

02:01.295 --> 02:03.471
[gasps]
Hey.

02:03.514 --> 02:05.386
She's sick again.

02:05.429 --> 02:06.735
Staying topside
is the only thing

02:06.778 --> 02:08.693
that seems to help.
[Inhales deeply]

02:08.737 --> 02:12.262
Get her to the stern
so she can see the horizon.

02:12.306 --> 02:15.265
[Metal groaning]

02:15.309 --> 02:16.440
No.

02:16.484 --> 02:18.790
[Turbines creaking]

02:18.834 --> 02:20.749
No, no, no.

02:20.792 --> 02:22.794
What's going on?
Why are we stopping?

02:22.838 --> 02:25.797
Just get her to the stern!

02:25.841 --> 02:27.625
Come on.

02:27.669 --> 02:34.676
♪

02:38.549 --> 02:40.638
[gun fires]

02:40.682 --> 02:42.205
[faint clang]

02:43.641 --> 02:46.427
[faint shouting]

02:46.470 --> 02:48.211
[gunshot]
[bullet pings]

02:48.255 --> 02:49.343
Hit the deck!

02:49.386 --> 02:51.345
[Sinister music]

02:51.388 --> 02:53.782
[bullets pinging]

02:53.825 --> 02:56.741
♪

02:56.785 --> 02:58.482
Are they shooting at us?

02:58.526 --> 03:00.745
[Glass shattering]
Get away from the window!

03:02.573 --> 03:03.661
[Bullets pinging]

03:03.705 --> 03:06.664
♪

03:06.708 --> 03:08.536
[both breathing heavily]

03:08.579 --> 03:11.539
[alarm trilling]

03:11.582 --> 03:12.801
She did it.

03:12.844 --> 03:16.326
[Tense music]

03:16.370 --> 03:18.546
We're tracking them.

03:18.589 --> 03:20.461
We finally got the bastards.

03:20.504 --> 03:22.245
Ten tons of illegal fish
and a video

03:22.289 --> 03:24.726
of those assholes
shooting at us.

03:24.769 --> 03:26.380
That's prison for sure, right?

03:26.423 --> 03:28.817
First we've got
to catch up to them,

03:28.860 --> 03:31.298
stop them before they unload.

03:31.341 --> 03:32.821
[Panting]

03:32.864 --> 03:35.867
Any idea how we're gonna
do that?

03:35.911 --> 03:37.826
[Steam hissing]

03:37.869 --> 03:39.480
Rusty?

03:39.523 --> 03:41.699
How's it looking down there?

03:41.743 --> 03:44.572
♪

03:44.615 --> 03:46.574
Thought we had a deal, Gwenn.

03:46.617 --> 03:49.838
I agree to fix her.
You agreed not to break her.

03:49.881 --> 03:53.407
I thought we were here
to do whatever it takes.

03:53.450 --> 03:55.452
Takes an engine
is what it takes, Gwenn.

03:55.496 --> 03:57.715
You do know how a ship works,
right?

03:57.759 --> 04:00.588
- Just tell me when...
- Need a hand here.

04:00.631 --> 04:04.505
♪

04:04.548 --> 04:06.463
Do you know
what the problem is?

04:06.507 --> 04:08.335
We just make it look
too damn easy.

04:08.378 --> 04:10.598
Hell, yeah.

04:10.641 --> 04:13.601
♪

04:13.644 --> 04:17.430
[breathing heavily]

04:17.474 --> 04:19.346
I think it's over.

04:19.389 --> 04:21.565
[Door creaking]

04:27.441 --> 04:29.443
I need to sit down
for a minute.

04:36.667 --> 04:39.453
Getting shot at...

04:39.496 --> 04:40.845
not what I signed up for.

04:40.889 --> 04:42.934
Tell me this doesn't happen
all the time.

04:42.978 --> 04:44.414
Don't ask me.

04:44.458 --> 04:45.676
This is my first time out.

04:45.720 --> 04:47.591
Are you guys all right?

04:47.635 --> 04:50.638
We're not shot,
if that's what you mean.

04:50.681 --> 04:52.553
They're gonna pay for that,
I promise!

04:52.596 --> 04:54.642
Dana, is everything okay?

04:55.904 --> 04:57.906
Ugh.

04:57.949 --> 05:00.430
This is gonna be
a long three months.

05:00.474 --> 05:01.475
[Gags]

05:03.868 --> 05:05.653
[whimpers]
You okay?

05:06.958 --> 05:08.699
[Gags]

05:11.702 --> 05:14.488
I never should have gotten
on this ship.

05:15.576 --> 05:17.447
What was I thinking?

05:17.491 --> 05:19.928
Aren't you, like,
their fish expert or something?

05:22.844 --> 05:24.672
Ichthyologist.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.371
Love fish.

05:28.415 --> 05:30.678
Hate the water.

05:30.721 --> 05:32.680
I know.

05:32.723 --> 05:35.465
The irony of it all
isn't lost on me.

05:36.858 --> 05:38.816
I'm a lab rat,
but my university

05:38.860 --> 05:40.731
makes me come out
once every three years

05:40.775 --> 05:43.560
for my accreditation.

05:43.604 --> 05:45.606
Must really love
what you do.

05:46.998 --> 05:49.349
Right now, not so much.

05:50.959 --> 05:53.483
So...

05:53.527 --> 05:57.487
what brings you to the middle
of the North Pacific?

05:57.531 --> 05:59.402
Um...

05:59.446 --> 06:01.970
I'm a med student.

06:02.013 --> 06:04.668
Well, I was.

06:04.712 --> 06:08.455
Um, actually...

06:08.498 --> 06:10.979
it's kind of a long story.
Did you see that?

06:11.022 --> 06:13.503
See what?

06:13.547 --> 06:14.852
There.

06:14.896 --> 06:16.724
[Foreboding music]

06:16.767 --> 06:19.727
[wind whistling]

06:19.770 --> 06:24.427
♪

06:24.471 --> 06:25.428
[door clangs]

06:25.472 --> 06:27.865
♪

06:27.909 --> 06:29.737
We're on it.

06:29.780 --> 06:32.435
I know.
I'm just trying

06:32.479 --> 06:34.655
to keep Gwenn
out of your hair.

06:34.698 --> 06:36.439
Hey, Gwenn, it's Dana.

06:36.483 --> 06:38.006
We'll have an estimate
on the engine in...

06:38.049 --> 06:39.442
One hour.

06:39.486 --> 06:41.531
Two hours.

06:41.575 --> 06:44.447
Listen, I need everyone
on the bridge.

06:44.491 --> 06:45.883
It's important.

06:45.927 --> 06:51.454
♪

06:51.498 --> 06:53.891
That's a hell of a storm.

06:53.935 --> 06:56.677
Over 100 miles wide.

06:56.720 --> 06:58.679
And growing.

06:58.722 --> 07:00.768
And we're directly
in its path.

07:00.811 --> 07:03.031
♪

07:03.074 --> 07:04.685
Getting shot at,

07:04.728 --> 07:05.947
no engine...

07:05.990 --> 07:08.776
this just keeps
getting better.

07:08.819 --> 07:10.517
You know what happens
if we hit that storm

07:10.560 --> 07:11.909
with no engine.

07:11.953 --> 07:15.043
Well aware, Rusty.

07:15.086 --> 07:16.914
- What happens?
- Without the engine,

07:16.958 --> 07:19.047
we can't turn into the waves.

07:19.090 --> 07:22.050
If we can't turn
into the waves...

07:22.093 --> 07:24.052
We capsize.

07:24.095 --> 07:27.490
♪

07:27.534 --> 07:28.970
How long do we have?

07:29.013 --> 07:32.060
At its current rate, I'd say
just under three hours.

07:32.103 --> 07:33.888
[Door clicks open]

07:34.932 --> 07:37.848
There's... there's something
in the water.

07:37.892 --> 07:44.899
♪

07:53.734 --> 07:56.519
Was it a boat you saw?

07:56.563 --> 07:58.608
It looked like...

07:58.652 --> 08:00.523
like someone was trying
to hold on to something

08:00.567 --> 08:01.698
in the water.

08:01.742 --> 08:03.004
It was hard to make out.

08:03.047 --> 08:05.876
But you're sure
you saw someone.

08:05.920 --> 08:07.965
It was nearly dark, but...
[sighs]

08:08.009 --> 08:10.968
I don't...
Michelle?

08:11.012 --> 08:13.580
Did you see anything
out there?

08:13.623 --> 08:15.103
Um...

08:15.146 --> 08:16.757
I'm not sure.
Look, I'm sorry,

08:16.800 --> 08:18.759
but I think we're wasting
our time here.

08:18.802 --> 08:21.109
It's not like we don't have
enough to deal with as it is.

08:21.152 --> 08:22.763
I'm with Rusty.

08:22.806 --> 08:23.894
It's not like there was
a distress call

08:23.938 --> 08:25.548
or anything, right?

08:25.592 --> 08:26.767
I mean, where would they
have come from?

08:26.810 --> 08:28.856
What about
the Chinese trawler?

08:28.899 --> 08:31.119
Someone could have fallen
overboard in the chaos.

08:31.162 --> 08:33.556
And they don't circle back
to get them?

08:33.600 --> 08:36.864
Look, I know
I saw something, all right?

08:36.907 --> 08:40.998
If it is a person, we can't
just leave them out there.

08:41.042 --> 08:43.174
You're right.
She's right.

08:43.217 --> 08:47.178
♪

08:47.222 --> 08:50.704
So how's this?
Uh, me, Erika, and Michelle,

08:50.747 --> 08:52.923
we take the lifeboat out;
We have a look.

08:52.967 --> 08:54.142
Everyone else focuses

08:54.185 --> 08:56.666
on getting the engine fixed.

08:56.710 --> 08:58.886
We come back the instant
you're up and running

08:58.929 --> 09:01.584
whether we find something
or not.

09:01.628 --> 09:02.716
If you go out in this,
you're never gonna

09:02.759 --> 09:03.978
find your way back.

09:04.021 --> 09:05.588
Keep the searchlight on.

09:05.632 --> 09:07.111
Make sure it's always
in sight.

09:07.155 --> 09:08.896
We have to know.

09:08.939 --> 09:10.680
Right?

09:10.724 --> 09:17.731
♪

09:18.732 --> 09:20.211
Hello?

09:20.255 --> 09:22.779
♪

09:22.823 --> 09:24.912
[motor puttering]

09:24.955 --> 09:27.131
Is anyone out there?

09:27.175 --> 09:28.698
[Suspenseful music]

09:28.742 --> 09:30.700
Hello?

09:30.744 --> 09:33.094
Can anybody hear me?

09:34.182 --> 09:37.054
Hello?

09:37.098 --> 09:39.622
[Steam hissing]

09:39.666 --> 09:42.886
♪

09:44.714 --> 09:46.890
[steam hissing]

09:46.934 --> 09:49.110
Here's the hose.

09:52.200 --> 09:53.897
Kat, the hose.

09:59.773 --> 10:02.776
- What if this doesn't work?
- It will work.

10:02.819 --> 10:05.082
Yeah, but what if it doesn't?

10:05.126 --> 10:07.084
Kat, I need you to focus.

10:07.128 --> 10:08.956
♪

10:08.999 --> 10:11.654
There's no engine we can't fix,
am I right?

10:11.698 --> 10:13.743
♪

10:13.787 --> 10:15.832
Am I right?

10:15.876 --> 10:17.747
You're right.

10:17.791 --> 10:18.835
Okay.

10:18.879 --> 10:20.228
Now, let's get this done.

10:20.271 --> 10:25.755
♪

10:25.799 --> 10:27.017
Hello?

10:27.061 --> 10:29.280
[Motor puttering]

10:29.324 --> 10:32.936
Hello?

10:32.980 --> 10:36.679
Is there anyone out there?

10:36.723 --> 10:38.159
Hello?

10:38.202 --> 10:40.770
Can anybody hear me?

10:40.814 --> 10:47.821
♪

10:52.826 --> 10:55.132
Thought you hated
the water.

10:55.176 --> 10:58.135
Yeah, don't remind me.

10:58.179 --> 11:00.703
♪

11:00.747 --> 11:02.705
Hello!

11:02.749 --> 11:05.012
Can anyone hear me?

11:05.055 --> 11:09.756
[Faint rumbling]

11:09.799 --> 11:12.193
Hey, do you hear that?

11:12.236 --> 11:14.021
♪

11:14.064 --> 11:16.153
They got the engine going.

11:16.197 --> 11:18.112
♪

11:18.155 --> 11:19.722
So we should be
heading back, right?

11:19.766 --> 11:21.898
Like you said.
We haven't been looking

11:21.942 --> 11:23.726
for that long.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.815
I'm sure we can spare
a few more minutes.

11:25.859 --> 11:26.947
Right?

11:26.990 --> 11:30.211
♪

11:30.254 --> 11:32.822
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

11:32.866 --> 11:34.171
Just stay calm.
I'm sure they'll have it

11:34.215 --> 11:35.738
powered up any...

11:35.782 --> 11:37.827
[shrieks]

11:37.871 --> 11:39.089
[sinister music]

11:39.133 --> 11:40.743
[gasps]
Michelle!

11:40.787 --> 11:41.962
Michelle!

11:42.005 --> 11:44.225
- Michelle?
- Michelle!

11:44.268 --> 11:45.879
♪

11:45.922 --> 11:47.184
Michelle!

11:47.228 --> 11:49.056
Michelle!

11:49.099 --> 11:50.884
♪

11:50.927 --> 11:52.755
See if you can find
a bigger clamp.

11:52.799 --> 11:54.975
Rusty?
What the hell happened?

11:55.018 --> 11:57.281
You happened, Gwenn.
Remember?

11:57.325 --> 11:58.761
We're just trying to fix it

11:58.805 --> 12:00.197
with what little
we've got, okay?

12:00.241 --> 12:02.112
- What about the generator?
- Its pump

12:02.156 --> 12:03.853
to the main fuel line
is shot.

12:03.897 --> 12:05.768
We told Gwenn already.

12:05.812 --> 12:07.204
Look, without
that searchlight,

12:07.248 --> 12:08.945
Dana's not gonna have
a hope in hell

12:08.989 --> 12:12.079
of finding her way back here.
We hear you,

12:12.122 --> 12:14.864
but one problem at a time,
all right?

12:14.908 --> 12:17.867
Oh, found one.
Here.

12:17.911 --> 12:20.870
[Tense music]

12:20.914 --> 12:23.003
♪

12:23.046 --> 12:25.309
- Michelle?
- Michelle!

12:25.353 --> 12:27.224
- Where is she?
- Michelle?

12:27.268 --> 12:29.009
Michelle!

12:29.052 --> 12:30.227
♪

12:30.271 --> 12:31.968
[muffled]
Michelle!

12:32.012 --> 12:34.101
[Panting]
Where are you?

12:34.144 --> 12:35.885
Michelle!

12:35.929 --> 12:37.234
Michelle!
[gasps]

12:37.278 --> 12:39.889
- Come on! Grab hold!
- Take my hand!

12:39.933 --> 12:42.022
- [Gasping]
- Come on!

12:42.065 --> 12:43.806
- Pull!
- [gasping]

12:43.850 --> 12:45.286
- [grunting]
- Pull!

12:45.329 --> 12:47.244
[Groans]

12:47.288 --> 12:49.899
[all panting]

12:49.943 --> 12:52.902
[coughing, gasping]
Oh, my God!

12:52.946 --> 12:55.383
I don't think...
[gasping, coughing]

12:55.426 --> 12:57.254
I'm a big fan
of the water either.

12:57.298 --> 12:59.822
[laughs]

12:59.866 --> 13:03.043
[engine roaring]

13:03.086 --> 13:05.828
♪

13:05.872 --> 13:07.351
The power's back on.

13:07.395 --> 13:10.877
They got the engine going.

13:10.920 --> 13:12.269
[Sinister music]

13:12.313 --> 13:14.924
[screaming]

13:14.968 --> 13:20.016
♪

13:20.060 --> 13:22.279
Is he alive?

13:22.323 --> 13:24.847
- [Gasping]
- This guy sure as hell

13:24.891 --> 13:27.284
didn't fall off
a fishing trawler.

13:27.328 --> 13:29.286
[All panting]

13:29.330 --> 13:31.941
I'm surprised he's still
alive, considering how cold

13:31.985 --> 13:33.464
that water is.
You got that right.

13:33.508 --> 13:36.076
Okay, we're gonna need
your help.

13:36.119 --> 13:38.165
Uh...

13:38.208 --> 13:41.168
[tense music]

13:41.211 --> 13:43.170
♪

13:43.213 --> 13:45.215
[shuddering]

13:45.259 --> 13:52.266
♪

13:58.925 --> 14:00.230
Okay.

14:00.274 --> 14:01.884
Come on, girl.

14:01.928 --> 14:03.320
You can do it.

14:03.364 --> 14:06.193
♪

14:06.236 --> 14:09.457
[engines revving]

14:09.500 --> 14:11.938
[muffled crash]
[waves splashing]

14:11.981 --> 14:14.941
[steam hissing]

14:14.984 --> 14:16.464
♪

14:16.507 --> 14:18.335
[metal clanging]

14:18.379 --> 14:19.380
[steam hissing]

14:19.423 --> 14:22.383
[grunting]

14:22.426 --> 14:25.212
♪

14:25.255 --> 14:27.954
Um, I need
the defib paddles.

14:27.997 --> 14:29.912
[Grunts]

14:29.956 --> 14:32.088
It's in the cabinet,
over there.

14:32.132 --> 14:35.048
Can someone get a knife
or scissors?

14:35.091 --> 14:36.919
♪

14:36.963 --> 14:39.139
How long could someone
survive in water that cold?

14:39.182 --> 14:41.228
[Panting]

14:41.271 --> 14:43.360
15 minutes.

14:43.404 --> 14:45.362
Maybe 30, tops.

14:45.406 --> 14:47.060
♪

14:47.103 --> 14:49.149
- S-so this guy
should be dead.

14:49.192 --> 14:51.455
Yeah, he's going to be
if you guys don't hurry.

14:51.499 --> 14:53.240
Here!

14:53.283 --> 14:55.285
♪

14:55.329 --> 14:56.983
[all scream]

14:57.026 --> 14:58.941
Sir, you need to sit back.

14:58.985 --> 15:00.203
- Let go!
- Please... please let go.

15:00.247 --> 15:02.031
Sir, you... you need
to let her go

15:02.075 --> 15:04.381
so we can help you, okay?
We're just trying to help!

15:04.425 --> 15:06.949
Calm down, sir!
No one is trying to hurt you,

15:06.993 --> 15:08.211
okay?
[hollers]

15:08.255 --> 15:11.258
[all screaming]

15:11.301 --> 15:14.261
[dramatic music]

15:14.304 --> 15:15.262
♪

15:15.305 --> 15:17.090
[grunts]

15:17.133 --> 15:20.049
♪

15:20.093 --> 15:22.530
[grunting]

15:22.573 --> 15:24.488
[screams]

15:24.532 --> 15:31.539
♪

15:33.802 --> 15:35.586
- [whimpering]
- Oh, God.

15:35.630 --> 15:37.501
[All panting]

15:37.545 --> 15:41.070
- Are you okay?
- Fine.

15:41.114 --> 15:44.421
[Groans]
I'm fine.

15:44.465 --> 15:46.510
Help Rusty!

15:46.554 --> 15:48.425
Okay.

15:48.469 --> 15:51.167
Let me take that.
I'm getting the rifle,

15:51.211 --> 15:54.301
and then I'm gonna go find him.
- A-alone?

15:54.344 --> 15:55.998
We'll all go.

15:56.042 --> 15:59.349
We'll take this deck
if you want to look topside.

15:59.393 --> 16:01.221
Okay.

16:01.264 --> 16:03.049
- Here, take this.
- There are bigger knives

16:03.092 --> 16:05.312
in the mess hall!
Rusty?

16:05.355 --> 16:08.315
[Tense music]

16:08.358 --> 16:10.056
♪

16:10.099 --> 16:12.449
What just happened here?

16:12.493 --> 16:14.321
I don't know.

16:14.364 --> 16:19.979
♪

16:27.160 --> 16:29.640
[waves crashing]

16:29.684 --> 16:32.643
[chain squeaking]

16:32.687 --> 16:35.037
♪

16:35.081 --> 16:36.473
[door creaks]

16:36.517 --> 16:41.522
♪

16:41.565 --> 16:44.046
[clears throat]

16:44.090 --> 16:47.049
[whispering]
Dana, wait up.

16:49.399 --> 16:50.400
[Object clatters]

16:50.444 --> 16:52.402
[gasps, grunts]

16:52.446 --> 16:53.621
N-no.

16:53.664 --> 16:55.057
No, no, no.

16:55.101 --> 16:57.494
No, my knife. No.

16:57.538 --> 16:59.366
[Foreboding music]

16:59.409 --> 17:01.281
Come on.

17:01.324 --> 17:04.588
♪

17:04.632 --> 17:06.155
[grunts]

17:06.199 --> 17:07.242
[metallic clatter]

17:07.287 --> 17:09.289
[whispering]
Dana?

17:09.332 --> 17:11.638
Dana, where'd you go?

17:11.682 --> 17:13.380
♪

17:13.423 --> 17:16.383
[chain squeaking]

17:16.425 --> 17:23.433
♪

17:28.395 --> 17:30.397
Dana, please.

17:30.440 --> 17:34.531
♪

17:34.575 --> 17:37.099
[shuddering]

17:37.143 --> 17:39.710
♪

17:39.754 --> 17:41.669
Dana?

17:41.712 --> 17:43.671
[Object clatters]

17:43.714 --> 17:50.199
♪

17:50.243 --> 17:51.722
[wind whistling]

17:51.766 --> 17:59.078
♪

18:00.557 --> 18:02.559
[gasps]

18:02.603 --> 18:05.345
- You need to stay close, okay?
- O-okay.

18:05.388 --> 18:08.348
[Suspenseful music]

18:08.391 --> 18:09.697
Hey!

18:09.740 --> 18:12.134
Hey, stop!

18:12.178 --> 18:14.571
♪

18:14.615 --> 18:16.138
Gwenn.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.358
Gwenn!
Wait!

18:18.401 --> 18:25.408
♪

18:34.287 --> 18:37.246
[gasping]

18:37.290 --> 18:42.730
♪

18:42.773 --> 18:44.688
Hey, asshole.

18:44.732 --> 18:47.256
[Grunts]
[screams]

18:47.300 --> 18:49.519
[sobs]

18:49.563 --> 18:52.479
[groans]

18:52.522 --> 18:54.655
[panting, gagging]

18:54.698 --> 18:57.658
[dark music]

18:57.701 --> 19:03.751
♪

19:03.794 --> 19:06.275
[knife clatters]

19:06.319 --> 19:13.282
♪

19:13.326 --> 19:15.502
Did... did you...

19:15.545 --> 19:16.764
♪

19:16.807 --> 19:19.375
What choice did I have,
right?

19:19.419 --> 19:21.377
♪

19:21.421 --> 19:23.205
[microphone feedback whines
over speakers]

19:23.249 --> 19:24.554
We need... we need some help
on the bridge!

19:24.598 --> 19:26.513
Now!

19:26.556 --> 19:33.563
♪

19:40.353 --> 19:43.356
[gasping]

19:43.399 --> 19:45.488
He stabbed Gwenn!

19:45.532 --> 19:48.274
- I-I'm gonna get
the first-aid kit.

19:48.317 --> 19:50.537
It's under the sink,
over there.

19:50.580 --> 19:52.452
[Tense music]

19:52.495 --> 19:53.540
[wind whistling]

19:53.583 --> 19:54.802
That psycho attacked her!

19:54.845 --> 19:57.848
We need to do something!

19:57.892 --> 20:00.721
We don't need to worry
about him any more.

20:00.764 --> 20:03.506
What?

20:03.550 --> 20:06.596
She, um...

20:06.640 --> 20:08.250
She killed him.

20:08.294 --> 20:09.251
What?

20:09.295 --> 20:12.559
♪

20:12.602 --> 20:15.301
Did to him what he was
gonna do to us.

20:15.344 --> 20:19.783
♪

20:19.827 --> 20:22.612
[wind whistling]

20:22.656 --> 20:29.663
♪

20:30.838 --> 20:32.405
What, we should have waited

20:32.448 --> 20:34.624
until he killed
one of us first?

20:35.582 --> 20:37.323
This is going to hurt.

20:37.366 --> 20:39.499
[Gasps]

20:39.542 --> 20:41.718
You should set
the autopilot.

20:41.762 --> 20:44.591
♪

20:44.634 --> 20:45.853
[computer beeps]

20:45.896 --> 20:48.595
♪

20:48.638 --> 20:49.857
[groans]
We need to call

20:49.900 --> 20:52.860
the Coast Guard.
Yeah, like hell we do.

20:52.903 --> 20:55.384
There is a dead man
on your ship.

20:55.428 --> 20:57.343
What are you gonna do,
just throw him overboard

20:57.386 --> 20:59.345
and pretend
none of this happened?

20:59.388 --> 21:00.737
Look, I did
what had to be done.

21:00.781 --> 21:02.913
Will the both of you
just stop?

21:02.957 --> 21:04.611
Okay?

21:04.654 --> 21:06.613
Let's get clear of this storm,

21:06.656 --> 21:09.311
and then we can decide
what's best to do.

21:09.355 --> 21:12.314
A few hours, it's not gonna
make a difference.

21:12.358 --> 21:13.620
♪

21:13.663 --> 21:14.882
Now, we need to get
that body inside

21:14.925 --> 21:16.840
before we hit any weather.

21:16.884 --> 21:18.799
You guys?

21:18.842 --> 21:20.844
What... what is it?

21:20.888 --> 21:23.412
He...

21:23.456 --> 21:25.545
he's, uh...

21:25.588 --> 21:27.851
What?

21:27.895 --> 21:29.897
He's gone.

21:29.940 --> 21:36.773
♪

21:36.817 --> 21:39.341
I thought you said...

21:39.385 --> 21:42.344
Well, he sure as hell
looked dead to me.

21:42.388 --> 21:43.911
Kill me.

21:43.954 --> 21:45.347
[Sinister music]

21:45.391 --> 21:47.393
What?

21:47.436 --> 21:48.655
♪

21:48.698 --> 21:50.787
When he grabbed me earlier

21:50.831 --> 21:52.441
in the sick bay...

21:52.485 --> 21:55.662
♪

21:55.705 --> 21:57.707
I-I think he said,

21:57.751 --> 21:59.448
"Kill me.

21:59.492 --> 22:01.581
"Kill yourselves.

22:01.624 --> 22:03.931
End this."

22:03.974 --> 22:06.716
♪

22:06.760 --> 22:09.502
[power whirs down]

22:09.545 --> 22:11.634
[thunder rumbling]

22:11.678 --> 22:15.551
[foreboding music]

22:15.595 --> 22:17.553
I thought the engine
was fixed.

22:17.597 --> 22:19.381
It was fixed.

22:19.425 --> 22:21.731
That man's still
out there somewhere.

22:21.775 --> 22:22.993
Lock those doors.

22:23.037 --> 22:25.387
[Alarm trilling]
Generator's kicked on.

22:25.431 --> 22:27.694
[Suspenseful music]

22:27.737 --> 22:28.999
Turn that off.

22:29.043 --> 22:31.741
♪

22:31.785 --> 22:33.656
[alarm stops]

22:33.700 --> 22:36.485
♪

22:36.529 --> 22:38.966
Okay, everyone just...

22:39.009 --> 22:41.838
take a breath.
Take a breath?

22:41.882 --> 22:43.971
Did you not hear
what he said to her?

22:44.014 --> 22:46.408
He was probably in shock.

22:46.452 --> 22:47.714
Delusional.

22:47.757 --> 22:49.498
Who knows what being
in the water that long

22:49.542 --> 22:50.847
did to him?

22:50.891 --> 22:51.892
Well, it sure as hell
didn't kill him

22:51.935 --> 22:52.893
like it should have, right?

22:52.936 --> 22:54.634
Right?

22:54.677 --> 22:56.549
Be careful with that, Kat.

22:56.592 --> 22:58.420
♪

22:58.464 --> 23:00.857
No, he shouldn't
have survived that.

23:00.901 --> 23:03.773
- What about the 12-inch blade
Rusty buried in his stomach?

23:03.817 --> 23:05.862
Should he have been able
to survive that?

23:05.906 --> 23:08.735
He crawled off somewhere,
okay?

23:08.778 --> 23:09.953
He crawled off and died.

23:09.997 --> 23:11.868
No one can survive
an injury like that.

23:11.912 --> 23:14.523
That's my point, Rusty.

23:14.567 --> 23:17.004
He should not have survived
in the first place.

23:17.047 --> 23:18.745
♪

23:18.788 --> 23:20.877
She's right.

23:20.921 --> 23:23.489
How do you explain that?

23:23.532 --> 23:25.969
Look, he's either dead,

23:26.013 --> 23:28.624
or he's not,
but none of that matters

23:28.668 --> 23:30.626
if we don't get
the damn engine fixed.

23:30.670 --> 23:34.891
That storm is gonna be on us
within the hour.

23:34.935 --> 23:37.894
Without the engine, we all know
what that means.

23:37.938 --> 23:40.549
Even if we call for help,
no one would ever

23:40.593 --> 23:41.898
get to us in time.

23:41.942 --> 23:43.857
♪

23:43.900 --> 23:45.815
Looks like it's up
to you and me.

23:45.859 --> 23:49.906
♪

23:49.950 --> 23:51.995
Like that's something new.

23:52.039 --> 23:54.041
Sparks and I will come
give you a hand.

23:54.084 --> 23:56.739
We will?

23:56.783 --> 24:01.483
♪

24:01.527 --> 24:04.007
[wind whistling]

24:04.051 --> 24:07.010
[tense music]

24:07.054 --> 24:14.061
♪

24:24.767 --> 24:27.770
[door clangs, creaks]

24:27.814 --> 24:34.821
♪

24:43.569 --> 24:44.831
Hey.

24:44.874 --> 24:46.136
♪

24:46.180 --> 24:48.965
You guys go ahead.

24:49.009 --> 24:51.881
I'm right behind you.
Where are you going?

24:51.925 --> 24:54.101
I need to find out
where our friend went.

24:54.144 --> 24:55.885
Shouldn't we all
stick together?

24:55.929 --> 24:57.583
We'll work a lot faster
if we're not

24:57.626 --> 24:58.932
constantly looking
over our shoulder.

24:58.975 --> 25:00.977
I won't be long.
Dana, wait.

25:01.021 --> 25:02.762
♪

25:02.805 --> 25:04.720
If he's not dead...

25:04.764 --> 25:06.113
you'll finish him, right?

25:06.156 --> 25:08.115
♪

25:08.158 --> 25:10.552
Get the engine fixed.

25:10.596 --> 25:13.163
♪

25:13.207 --> 25:15.165
[sighs]

25:15.209 --> 25:22.521
♪

25:29.136 --> 25:32.139
[breathing shakily]

25:32.182 --> 25:39.538
♪

25:44.804 --> 25:46.936
[water splashing]

25:46.980 --> 25:49.678
[wind whistling]

25:49.722 --> 25:56.729
♪

26:06.739 --> 26:09.698
[hatch creaking]

26:09.742 --> 26:16.749
♪

26:36.769 --> 26:38.248
Genny's gonna need gas.

26:38.292 --> 26:40.990
[Power whirs down]

26:41.034 --> 26:43.689
God damn it.
[sighs]

26:43.732 --> 26:48.258
♪

26:48.302 --> 26:51.087
Perfect.
Just perfect.

26:51.131 --> 26:52.872
♪

26:52.915 --> 26:55.004
[door creaks]

26:55.048 --> 26:57.877
What the hell is going on
down there?

26:57.920 --> 27:00.183
Generator's out of gas.
We're on it.

27:00.227 --> 27:02.664
♪

27:02.708 --> 27:05.711
[breathing shakily]

27:14.241 --> 27:15.938
I'll get the gas.

27:19.159 --> 27:21.117
I need a little light
over here.

27:21.161 --> 27:23.163
All right.

27:25.948 --> 27:28.951
[Metal creaking]

27:28.995 --> 27:31.693
♪

27:31.737 --> 27:33.652
[faint metallic bang]
[gasps]

27:40.746 --> 27:42.791
We're gonna get
through this, right?

27:42.835 --> 27:44.924
Yeah.

27:44.967 --> 27:47.056
You know why?

27:47.100 --> 27:50.016
'Cause we're just
too damn good.

27:50.059 --> 27:52.061
Damn right we are.

27:52.105 --> 27:55.761
[Gas splashing]

27:55.804 --> 28:02.028
♪

28:02.071 --> 28:04.683
[faint metallic clang,
crash]

28:05.771 --> 28:07.686
Sparks?

28:09.209 --> 28:10.993
Sparks!

28:11.037 --> 28:12.081
Sparks?

28:12.125 --> 28:14.780
This is no time for jokes.

28:18.218 --> 28:20.176
[Foreboding music]

28:20.220 --> 28:23.136
[generator whirring]

28:23.179 --> 28:25.747
♪

28:25.791 --> 28:27.183
What the hell happened?

28:27.227 --> 28:34.234
♪

28:35.931 --> 28:39.021
Why would someone do this?

28:39.065 --> 28:41.197
We'll never get this fixed
in time.

28:41.241 --> 28:42.895
♪

28:42.938 --> 28:45.114
We'll never get this
fixed in time.

28:45.158 --> 28:48.988
♪

28:49.031 --> 28:50.816
What are we gonna do?

28:50.859 --> 28:52.861
[Loud bang]

28:52.905 --> 28:54.210
♪

28:54.254 --> 28:56.386
He's here!

28:56.430 --> 28:58.867
He's... he's in here somewhere.

28:58.911 --> 29:01.217
What?

29:01.261 --> 29:03.219
Oh, God.
[breathing heavily]

29:03.263 --> 29:05.395
♪

29:05.439 --> 29:07.006
What happened here?

29:07.049 --> 29:09.182
We're in serious trouble.

29:09.225 --> 29:12.185
[Tense music]

29:12.228 --> 29:17.886
♪

29:17.930 --> 29:19.888
Where's Sparks?

29:19.932 --> 29:22.021
I don't know.

29:22.064 --> 29:23.413
She was just here.

29:23.457 --> 29:25.241
♪

29:25.285 --> 29:26.895
Sparks?

29:26.939 --> 29:33.946
♪

29:40.213 --> 29:43.259
[door creaking]

29:46.872 --> 29:48.395
Sparks?

29:48.438 --> 29:50.440
Are you in here?

29:50.484 --> 29:53.139
♪

29:53.182 --> 29:56.359
[door creaking]

29:56.403 --> 29:58.231
Sparks.

29:58.274 --> 30:05.281
♪

30:13.986 --> 30:16.292
[screams]
What is it?

30:16.336 --> 30:17.990
- [Groans]
- Oh, God.

30:18.033 --> 30:19.295
Sparks.

30:19.339 --> 30:21.950
What happened?

30:21.994 --> 30:25.214
[Stammers]
I don't know.

30:25.258 --> 30:27.086
She's hurt.

30:27.129 --> 30:28.914
- [Growls]
- [yelps]

30:28.957 --> 30:30.959
Let her go!

30:31.003 --> 30:32.482
- [Screaming]
- Get him off!

30:32.526 --> 30:34.397
[All shouting]

30:34.441 --> 30:37.923
- [screaming]
- [hollers]

30:37.966 --> 30:39.925
[body thuds]

30:39.968 --> 30:42.928
[all breathing heavily]

30:42.971 --> 30:45.931
[tense music]

30:45.974 --> 30:49.238
♪

30:49.282 --> 30:51.937
I think he's dead.

30:51.980 --> 30:54.983
[Gunshot]
[all scream]

30:56.245 --> 30:58.334
I think so too.

30:58.378 --> 31:01.337
[Wind whistling]

31:01.381 --> 31:04.340
[foreboding music]

31:04.384 --> 31:11.391
♪

31:14.481 --> 31:16.526
From here on in,
I don't think anyone

31:16.570 --> 31:18.267
should be touching him.
What do you mean,

31:18.311 --> 31:19.312
we shouldn't be touching him?

31:19.355 --> 31:21.967
We've all touched him.

31:22.010 --> 31:23.533
♪

31:23.577 --> 31:24.534
See this?

31:24.578 --> 31:27.276
♪

31:27.320 --> 31:29.017
Was that there before?

31:29.061 --> 31:31.150
♪

31:31.193 --> 31:33.239
Um...

31:33.282 --> 31:36.024
we never had a chance
to look that closely.

31:36.068 --> 31:39.071
♪

31:39.114 --> 31:42.552
Dana, she just said
not to touch him.

31:42.596 --> 31:49.908
♪

31:55.478 --> 31:57.567
Well, that's not good.

31:57.611 --> 32:04.923
♪

32:07.099 --> 32:09.275
[sighs]

32:09.318 --> 32:12.104
There's nothing we can do
about this now.

32:12.147 --> 32:14.541
We need to focus on getting
the engine fixed.

32:14.584 --> 32:16.412
♪

32:16.456 --> 32:18.023
Kat, what the hell
are you doing?

32:18.066 --> 32:19.546
I'm getting off the ship!

32:19.589 --> 32:22.549
You should all do the same!
Don't be stupid, Kat!

32:22.592 --> 32:25.030
Go the other way!
Cut her off!

32:25.073 --> 32:28.033
[Tense music]

32:28.076 --> 32:35.083
♪

32:45.485 --> 32:48.444
[sinister music]

32:48.488 --> 32:53.275
♪

32:53.319 --> 32:56.278
[thunder rumbling]

32:56.322 --> 32:58.280
[foreboding music]

32:58.324 --> 33:00.065
[door creaks]

33:00.108 --> 33:03.068
[panting]

33:03.111 --> 33:08.464
♪

33:08.508 --> 33:11.467
[waves crashing]

33:11.511 --> 33:18.126
♪

33:18.170 --> 33:20.389
Oh, God.
Kat.

33:20.433 --> 33:23.175
You need to stop, okay?

33:23.218 --> 33:25.481
You're not thinking
this through.

33:25.525 --> 33:28.223
I'm getting off this ship,
Rusty,

33:28.267 --> 33:29.485
with or without you.

33:29.529 --> 33:32.140
And go where?

33:32.184 --> 33:34.142
♪

33:34.186 --> 33:35.491
She's right, Kat.

33:35.535 --> 33:37.363
♪

33:37.406 --> 33:41.149
Closest land
is over 600 miles away.

33:42.237 --> 33:45.414
You'd run out of gas
long before then.

33:46.372 --> 33:49.288
I guess I'll have
to take my chances.

33:49.331 --> 33:52.334
You really think you're gonna
make it out there in this?

33:52.378 --> 33:55.468
If you care so much,
help me with the bigger boat.

33:55.511 --> 33:58.645
In either boat, you're gonna
end up in the water.

33:58.688 --> 34:00.168
♪

34:00.212 --> 34:02.301
Then you're done for.

34:02.344 --> 34:04.172
That's a guarantee.

34:04.216 --> 34:07.088
If we stay on this ship,
we're all done for.

34:07.132 --> 34:09.308
Can't you all see that?

34:09.351 --> 34:12.398
I mean, who knows
what that guy had?

34:12.440 --> 34:14.704
For all we know...

34:14.748 --> 34:17.098
we have it now too.

34:17.141 --> 34:18.534
Kat...

34:18.578 --> 34:21.233
the only hope in hell
we have of surviving this

34:21.275 --> 34:24.235
is if we get that engine
going again.

34:24.279 --> 34:26.716
I'll never be able
to do it without you.

34:26.760 --> 34:28.456
♪

34:28.501 --> 34:30.242
You don't really think
that mess down there

34:30.284 --> 34:31.721
can be fixed, right?

34:31.764 --> 34:33.549
It can.

34:33.592 --> 34:36.552
If you help me, it can.

34:36.596 --> 34:39.293
[Wind blowing]

34:40.730 --> 34:43.472
Just stay back, all right?

34:43.516 --> 34:45.126
♪

34:45.170 --> 34:48.434
Going out there
is a death sentence.

34:48.476 --> 34:51.306
But if that's what you want...

34:51.350 --> 34:54.179
and you want to leave us
out here to fend for ourselves,

34:54.222 --> 34:57.182
then we're not gonna stop you.

34:58.183 --> 35:01.229
[Waves crashing]

35:03.188 --> 35:04.754
I'm...

35:04.798 --> 35:06.408
[thunder rumbling]

35:06.452 --> 35:08.758
I just... I don't want
to die, okay?

35:08.802 --> 35:11.413
♪

35:11.457 --> 35:13.720
Not out here.

35:13.763 --> 35:16.592
Not like this.

35:16.636 --> 35:20.683
Then I suggest
we all get busy.

35:20.727 --> 35:23.773
That is, if we're done
with the theatrics.

35:23.817 --> 35:31.129
♪

35:40.225 --> 35:41.443
Sparks?

35:41.487 --> 35:42.705
You head up to the radio room.

35:42.749 --> 35:44.403
We're gonna send
that mayday, okay?

35:44.446 --> 35:46.622
I'll try and steer us
into the waves.

35:46.666 --> 35:49.277
Maybe buy us some time.
I'll come help you.

35:49.321 --> 35:51.410
- Okay.
- You guys go with Rusty.

35:51.453 --> 35:54.195
She's gonna need all the hands
she can get.

35:54.239 --> 35:56.197
I'm... I'm sorry.

35:56.241 --> 35:58.330
I can't go back in there.

35:58.373 --> 36:00.636
Not until that body's gone.

36:00.680 --> 36:02.812
♪

36:02.856 --> 36:04.510
Well, does anyone
have a problem now

36:04.553 --> 36:06.642
with throwing him overboard?
Actually,

36:06.686 --> 36:08.514
that's the last thing
we should be doing.

36:08.557 --> 36:10.472
Well, I've had
just about enough

36:10.516 --> 36:13.519
of your holier-than-thou,
self-righteous bullshit.

36:13.562 --> 36:15.608
He was sick, right?

36:15.651 --> 36:19.264
And we've all come
in contact with him.

36:19.307 --> 36:21.266
If he is contagious,

36:21.309 --> 36:24.747
we need to know with what
before we all end up like him.

36:24.791 --> 36:27.315
Is that something
you can do?

36:27.359 --> 36:28.621
♪

36:28.664 --> 36:30.623
Michelle can do an autopsy.

36:30.666 --> 36:32.233
I'll assist her.

36:32.277 --> 36:34.322
Wait, what?

36:34.366 --> 36:36.237
I'm not qualified to do that.

36:36.281 --> 36:38.587
I barely got through
half of med school.

36:38.631 --> 36:41.286
♪

36:41.329 --> 36:43.288
I can't.

36:43.331 --> 36:49.685
♪

36:49.729 --> 36:53.298
You're gonna be okay
to do this, right?

36:53.341 --> 36:54.690
Uh...

36:54.734 --> 36:56.301
[stammers]

36:56.344 --> 36:58.390
You don't understand. Uh...

36:58.433 --> 37:00.479
I-I really don't do well

37:00.522 --> 37:03.264
in... in stressful situations.

37:03.308 --> 37:05.701
That's why I-I washed out
of med school.

37:05.745 --> 37:07.703
We're gonna take it slow.

37:07.747 --> 37:09.618
One step at a time.

37:09.662 --> 37:11.272
Okay?

37:11.316 --> 37:13.448
One step at a time.

37:13.492 --> 37:15.320
Pull away his shirt.

37:15.363 --> 37:17.670
I'm gonna collect
some data, okay?

37:17.713 --> 37:19.454
Okay.

37:19.498 --> 37:22.457
[Suspenseful music]

37:22.501 --> 37:24.372
[grunts]

37:24.416 --> 37:26.374
♪

37:26.418 --> 37:27.680
Mayday, mayday, mayday.

37:27.723 --> 37:29.421
This is the "Amphitrite"
requesting

37:29.464 --> 37:30.813
immediate assistance.

37:30.857 --> 37:33.555
We're broken down in the path
of a Category 3 storm

37:33.599 --> 37:35.644
at 2-5 degrees

37:35.688 --> 37:38.430
3-2.9 minutes north,

37:38.473 --> 37:41.694
1-4-2 degrees
4-4.9 minutes east.

37:41.737 --> 37:44.740
Again, we are requesting
immediate assistance.

37:44.784 --> 37:49.745
[Static crackling]

37:49.789 --> 37:51.834
I'm telling you,
there's no one out there.

37:51.878 --> 37:53.619
No one was stupid enough
to hang around

37:53.662 --> 37:56.535
in the path of this storm.
Just keep trying, okay?

37:56.578 --> 37:59.581
[Wind howling]
[sighs]

38:02.454 --> 38:05.457
[foreboding music]

38:05.500 --> 38:07.633
♪

38:07.676 --> 38:08.721
Mayday, mayday.

38:08.764 --> 38:09.939
This is the "Amphitrite"

38:09.983 --> 38:11.724
requesting
immediate assistance.

38:11.767 --> 38:13.552
Does anyone copy?

38:18.470 --> 38:19.601
Mayday, mayday.

38:19.645 --> 38:20.689
This is the "Amphitrite"

38:20.733 --> 38:21.951
requesting
immediate assistance.

38:21.995 --> 38:25.346
- [Sighs]
- You doing okay?

38:25.390 --> 38:26.739
I think so.

38:26.782 --> 38:28.654
The ballasts are full now,

38:28.697 --> 38:31.396
so it should stabilize us.

38:31.439 --> 38:33.702
At least for a while.

38:33.746 --> 38:34.790
[Metal groaning]

38:34.834 --> 38:36.879
No, I mean...

38:36.923 --> 38:39.404
I mean, are you doing okay?
Mayday, mayday.

38:39.447 --> 38:40.492
This is the "Amphitrite"

38:40.535 --> 38:41.710
requesting
immediate assistance.

38:41.754 --> 38:42.972
We're broken down
in the path

38:43.016 --> 38:44.626
of a Category 3 storm.
[sniffles]

38:44.670 --> 38:46.715
You mean, uh...

38:46.759 --> 38:49.979
am I doing okay
with the fact that...

38:50.023 --> 38:54.549
if it wasn't for me,
we wouldn't be in this mess?

38:54.593 --> 38:58.466
Am I doing okay
with being the one responsible

38:58.510 --> 39:00.686
for possibly getting
us all killed?

39:00.729 --> 39:04.385
No one is blaming you.

39:04.429 --> 39:07.388
I'm blaming me.

39:07.432 --> 39:09.956
This is my ship.

39:09.999 --> 39:12.480
It's my responsibility,

39:12.524 --> 39:14.482
and, uh...

39:14.526 --> 39:15.483
[metal groaning]

39:15.527 --> 39:16.832
I pushed...

39:16.876 --> 39:18.921
I pushed too hard this time.

39:18.965 --> 39:21.489
No one could have known
what was gonna happen

39:21.533 --> 39:23.404
when we let that man on board.

39:23.448 --> 39:26.755
♪

39:26.799 --> 39:29.410
We did what was right.

39:29.454 --> 39:31.847
[Melancholy music]

39:31.891 --> 39:34.502
Dad would have done
the same thing.

39:34.546 --> 39:37.462
♪

39:37.505 --> 39:40.421
When did, uh,
my little sister

39:40.465 --> 39:42.554
get so grown up?

39:42.597 --> 39:44.033
♪

39:44.077 --> 39:46.514
I had to grow up.

39:46.558 --> 39:48.603
I had to look after you.

39:51.040 --> 39:53.739
Dana, this is Michelle.

39:53.782 --> 39:55.958
We got something down here
you guys might want

39:56.002 --> 39:57.046
to have a look at.

39:57.090 --> 39:58.700
Go.
I've got this.

39:58.744 --> 40:00.528
[Clears throat]

40:00.572 --> 40:02.704
I'll be right there.

40:02.748 --> 40:05.707
[Tense music]

40:05.751 --> 40:09.711
♪

40:09.755 --> 40:11.539
Mayday, mayday.

40:11.583 --> 40:12.758
This is the "Amphitrite"

40:12.801 --> 40:14.716
requesting
immediate assistance.

40:14.760 --> 40:17.893
We're broken down in the path
of a Category 3 storm.

40:17.937 --> 40:20.722
Does anyone copy?

40:20.766 --> 40:22.637
♪

40:22.681 --> 40:25.640
[metal clanking]

40:25.684 --> 40:32.691
♪

40:38.740 --> 40:40.786
You really think
that's necessary?

40:40.829 --> 40:43.876
I've had enough surprises
for one day, thank you.

40:45.530 --> 40:48.489
Anybody tries to open
one of these doors,

40:48.533 --> 40:49.969
I want to know about it.

40:53.755 --> 40:56.105
Do you think you're ready
to get to work now?

40:56.149 --> 40:58.107
[Scoffs]
You think you've really got

40:58.151 --> 41:00.806
a way to fix that damn thing?

41:00.849 --> 41:02.111
♪

41:02.155 --> 41:03.939
[ship creaking]

41:03.983 --> 41:05.811
♪

41:05.854 --> 41:08.814
[foreboding music]

41:08.857 --> 41:11.860
♪

41:11.904 --> 41:13.949
You doing okay?

41:13.993 --> 41:16.604
I think so.

41:16.648 --> 41:18.824
[Ship creaking]

41:18.867 --> 41:25.047
♪

41:25.091 --> 41:28.094
[knocking]

41:33.752 --> 41:35.580
Uh...

41:35.623 --> 41:38.496
uh, it's at the... at the bottom
of the door.

41:39.105 --> 41:41.803
We found it
in his pants pocket.

41:41.847 --> 41:45.154
♪

41:45.198 --> 41:47.809
I doubt this will
power on, but...

41:47.853 --> 41:50.029
maybe Sparks can get something
off the SIM card.

41:51.639 --> 41:53.902
The other one is just
Sparks' video camera.

41:53.946 --> 41:55.817
We found it on the floor
in here.

41:55.861 --> 41:58.124
Maybe there's something
of use on it.

41:58.167 --> 42:00.561
Uh, I-I'd wear gloves
if you're gonna be handling

42:00.605 --> 42:02.911
either one of them,
just to be safe.

42:02.955 --> 42:05.610
Did you guys
find anything yet?

42:05.653 --> 42:06.828
[Ship groans]

42:06.872 --> 42:08.700
Ugh.

42:08.743 --> 42:10.615
♪

42:10.658 --> 42:11.920
Uh...

42:11.964 --> 42:14.009
I should get back.

42:14.053 --> 42:18.753
♪

42:18.797 --> 42:20.929
Let us know as soon
as you find something, okay?

42:20.973 --> 42:23.192
Okay.

42:23.236 --> 42:30.199
♪

42:30.243 --> 42:34.029
How many more do you need
for the biopsy?

42:34.073 --> 42:36.162
This should do it.

42:36.205 --> 42:43.561
♪

42:50.785 --> 42:53.745
- Can you reach it?
- I think so.

42:55.268 --> 42:58.053
[Ship groans]

42:58.097 --> 42:59.838
Rusty, you hear that?

43:02.231 --> 43:04.843
It's just the rudder shaft
sending vibrations

43:04.886 --> 43:06.758
through the hull.

43:06.801 --> 43:08.716
[Suspenseful music]

43:08.760 --> 43:11.937
[eerie groaning]

43:11.980 --> 43:13.678
♪

43:13.721 --> 43:15.070
Got it.
[grunts]

43:15.114 --> 43:16.245
[valve squeaking]

43:16.289 --> 43:18.639
[eerie, wheezing cry]

43:18.683 --> 43:19.858
♪

43:19.901 --> 43:21.903
Rusty, you there?

43:21.947 --> 43:28.780
♪

43:28.823 --> 43:30.782
Rusty?

43:30.825 --> 43:37.832
♪

43:52.325 --> 43:55.284
[foreboding music]

43:55.328 --> 43:57.243
♪

43:57.286 --> 43:59.724
Rusty, you still in here?

43:59.767 --> 44:06.774
♪

44:10.952 --> 44:12.998
Rusty?

44:13.041 --> 44:20.048
♪

44:22.921 --> 44:24.313
Mayday.

44:24.357 --> 44:26.098
Mayday, mayday.

44:26.141 --> 44:27.752
This is the "Amphitrite"

44:27.795 --> 44:29.101
requesting
immediate assistance.

44:29.144 --> 44:31.190
Is there anyone out there?

44:31.233 --> 44:33.758
[Wind howling]
[waves crashing]

44:33.801 --> 44:35.977
Mayday.

44:36.021 --> 44:38.980
Mayday, mayday.

44:39.024 --> 44:41.896
[Waves crashing]

44:41.940 --> 44:44.290
The SAT phone
was in his pocket.

44:44.333 --> 44:46.335
You think we can get anything
off the SIM card?

44:46.379 --> 44:49.034
- I-if it's not
too damaged, yeah.

44:49.077 --> 44:51.297
[Breathing heavily]
Hey, give me a hand here.

44:51.340 --> 44:53.255
[Dramatic music]

44:53.299 --> 44:54.953
Michelle said
to put gloves on

44:54.996 --> 44:56.302
before touching it.

44:56.345 --> 44:58.913
♪

44:58.957 --> 45:01.133
[hoarsely]
Copy that.

45:01.176 --> 45:04.832
♪

45:04.876 --> 45:07.748
Each cluster
is proportionally the same,

45:07.792 --> 45:09.271
but each new cluster
is slightly larger

45:09.315 --> 45:11.056
than the previous.

45:11.099 --> 45:14.363
An infection or disease
wouldn't spread like that.

45:14.407 --> 45:16.844
No, it wouldn't.

45:16.888 --> 45:19.325
[Suspenseful music]

45:19.368 --> 45:20.892
What do you think it is?

45:20.935 --> 45:23.895
♪

45:23.938 --> 45:26.027
I was hoping you'd be able
to tell me.

45:26.071 --> 45:28.856
♪

45:28.900 --> 45:31.076
Face your fears, right?

45:31.119 --> 45:35.080
♪

45:35.123 --> 45:37.865
[sighs]

45:37.909 --> 45:44.916
♪

45:45.830 --> 45:48.049
[breathing heavily]
You've got this.

45:48.093 --> 45:49.398
[Exhales sharply]

45:49.442 --> 45:52.227
[grunts]

45:52.271 --> 45:59.278
♪

46:02.934 --> 46:05.937
[sniffling, breathing heavily]

46:05.980 --> 46:08.940
[wind howling]

46:08.983 --> 46:15.990
♪

46:19.428 --> 46:21.343
[grunts]

46:21.387 --> 46:25.870
♪

46:25.913 --> 46:28.089
Let's get this over with.

46:28.133 --> 46:32.267
♪

46:32.311 --> 46:35.270
[foreboding music]

46:35.314 --> 46:40.145
♪

46:40.188 --> 46:43.104
Everything except the heart
is atrophied.

46:43.148 --> 46:45.280
♪

46:45.324 --> 46:47.848
That's not possible.

46:47.892 --> 46:52.200
♪

46:52.244 --> 46:54.376
Don't stop now.

46:54.420 --> 46:56.291
[Breathing heavily]

46:56.335 --> 46:58.424
Almost there.

46:58.467 --> 47:01.993
♪

47:02.036 --> 47:05.213
[bones snapping]

47:05.257 --> 47:07.955
Just breathe, okay?
[grunting]

47:07.999 --> 47:10.871
[bones snapping]

47:10.915 --> 47:12.394
Here.

47:12.438 --> 47:18.400
♪

47:18.444 --> 47:21.229
[grunts]

47:21.273 --> 47:24.319
[grunting]

47:24.363 --> 47:25.930
[bones snapping]

47:25.973 --> 47:28.149
Come on!

47:28.193 --> 47:30.499
[Grunting]
There.

47:30.543 --> 47:37.855
♪

47:42.511 --> 47:43.512
[bones cracking]

47:43.556 --> 47:45.514
[grunts]

47:45.558 --> 47:52.870
♪

47:54.393 --> 47:57.352
[sinister music]

47:57.396 --> 48:02.444
♪

48:02.488 --> 48:04.969
What is that?

48:08.407 --> 48:09.974
[Sinister musical sting]

48:10.017 --> 48:12.063
[both gasp]

48:12.106 --> 48:13.107
♪

48:13.151 --> 48:15.022
[gasping]

48:15.066 --> 48:17.024
I can't breathe.
Michelle, you need

48:17.068 --> 48:19.244
to leave your mask on!
I can't breathe.

48:19.287 --> 48:21.072
[Hyperventilating]
Michelle!

48:21.115 --> 48:23.465
Leave your mask on!
No!

48:23.509 --> 48:25.511
No!
Leave it on, Michelle!

48:25.554 --> 48:28.514
[Hyperventilating]

48:28.557 --> 48:30.559
♪

48:30.603 --> 48:32.083
Oh, God, get it off!

48:32.126 --> 48:34.999
- Michelle, go!
- [screams]

48:35.042 --> 48:38.350
♪

48:38.393 --> 48:41.353
[both panting]

48:41.396 --> 48:48.403
♪

48:53.539 --> 48:56.542
[flesh squelching]

48:56.585 --> 49:00.589
♪

49:00.633 --> 49:03.070
What the hell is that?

49:03.114 --> 49:10.121
♪

49:12.514 --> 49:15.169
[steam hissing]

49:15.213 --> 49:17.432
Rusty, can you guys
top off the generator?

49:17.476 --> 49:20.000
Looks like
she's almost out.

49:20.044 --> 49:21.523
[Generator whirring]

49:21.567 --> 49:23.308
Rusty?

49:23.351 --> 49:25.136
Kat?

49:25.179 --> 49:27.442
Do you copy?

49:27.486 --> 49:30.445
[Foreboding music]

49:30.489 --> 49:33.057
♪

49:33.100 --> 49:35.059
Oh, son of a bitch.

49:35.102 --> 49:36.364
[Breathing heavily]

49:36.408 --> 49:38.366
[flashlight clicks]

49:38.410 --> 49:41.369
[breathing shakily]

49:41.413 --> 49:45.373
♪

49:45.417 --> 49:47.288
[door clatters open]

49:47.332 --> 49:50.291
[wrenches clinking]

49:50.335 --> 49:53.338
[ship creaking]

49:55.079 --> 49:58.082
[metal groaning]

49:59.083 --> 50:01.476
Rusty?

50:01.520 --> 50:04.392
Kat?

50:04.436 --> 50:06.655
You guys in here?

50:06.699 --> 50:10.007
[Metal creaking, groaning]

50:14.533 --> 50:16.535
Rusty.

50:18.624 --> 50:20.191
Kat.

50:22.541 --> 50:24.151
[Liquid sloshes]

50:24.195 --> 50:27.198
[wind whistling]

50:28.590 --> 50:31.637
[generator whirring]

50:35.119 --> 50:37.512
Rusty!

50:37.556 --> 50:39.384
Kat!

50:47.609 --> 50:50.612
[Foreboding music]

50:50.656 --> 50:56.140
♪

50:56.183 --> 50:58.098
Hey, Gwenn?

50:58.142 --> 50:59.360
It's Dana.

50:59.404 --> 51:01.145
Uh, Rusty and Kat
aren't down here.

51:01.188 --> 51:03.234
Are... are they on the bridge?

51:03.277 --> 51:06.454
[Static crackling]

51:06.498 --> 51:09.370
Gwenn, are you there?

51:09.414 --> 51:11.372
[Wind whistling]

51:11.416 --> 51:12.547
Don't move.

51:12.591 --> 51:13.722
[Gun cocking]

51:13.766 --> 51:15.463
I said don't move.

51:15.507 --> 51:17.378
Gwenn, you don't need
to do this.

51:17.422 --> 51:19.467
She should have
said something.

51:19.511 --> 51:21.252
Gwenn, please.

51:21.295 --> 51:22.731
[Door clicks open]

51:22.775 --> 51:24.733
What the hell is going on?

51:24.777 --> 51:27.171
She's got the spots
on her arm

51:27.214 --> 51:28.737
and she didn't bother
to tell anyone.

51:28.781 --> 51:31.262
She's been walking around
this whole time

51:31.305 --> 51:33.264
and hasn't said a thing.

51:33.307 --> 51:35.440
[Tense music]

51:35.483 --> 51:38.182
Is that true?

51:38.225 --> 51:40.401
I...
[inhales shakily]

51:40.445 --> 51:41.489
Go ahead.

51:41.533 --> 51:43.230
Show her.

51:43.274 --> 51:45.276
♪

51:45.319 --> 51:48.279
I said show her.
All right.

51:48.322 --> 51:53.240
♪

51:53.284 --> 51:55.590
All right.
[breathing shakily]

51:55.634 --> 52:00.421
♪

52:00.465 --> 52:02.423
I feel fine.
You have got

52:02.467 --> 52:03.729
a damn disease.

52:03.772 --> 52:05.470
You are not fine.

52:05.513 --> 52:07.515
Everyone just stop,
all right?

52:07.559 --> 52:09.213
Just stop.
Get the hell out

52:09.256 --> 52:11.780
of the way, Erika.
It's not a disease.

52:11.824 --> 52:13.695
[Ship groans]

52:13.739 --> 52:16.437
[both groan]

52:16.481 --> 52:18.526
It's not a disease.

52:18.570 --> 52:20.572
I think...

52:20.615 --> 52:22.617
I think it's a bite mark.

52:22.661 --> 52:24.315
A bite mark?

52:24.358 --> 52:26.795
From what?
I don't know.

52:26.839 --> 52:29.798
But something was feeding
on that man's body,

52:29.842 --> 52:33.280
and as it grew,
its bite marks got larger.

52:33.324 --> 52:35.456
The three spots?

52:35.500 --> 52:37.284
It got larger.

52:37.328 --> 52:39.286
It must have tried moving on
to Sparks as a new food source,

52:39.330 --> 52:41.375
but Dana scared it off
in the engine room

52:41.419 --> 52:43.551
before it could finish
attaching or bond itself.

52:43.595 --> 52:45.379
This...

52:45.423 --> 52:46.815
is bullshit.

52:46.859 --> 52:48.730
That man was sick,

52:48.774 --> 52:50.384
plain and simple.

52:50.428 --> 52:52.647
Now Sparks has probably
infected the rest of us.

52:52.691 --> 52:54.562
We saw it, all right?

52:54.606 --> 52:57.217
We saw it inside the man
when we cut him open.

52:57.261 --> 52:59.611
It looked like...

52:59.654 --> 53:02.222
like it was trying
to keep him alive.

53:02.266 --> 53:04.268
[Muffled crash]

53:04.311 --> 53:07.271
[boat groaning]

53:07.314 --> 53:08.489
[waves crashing]

53:08.533 --> 53:10.578
[metal creaking]

53:10.622 --> 53:13.538
I think that's how
he survived in the water.

53:13.581 --> 53:15.627
It was keeping him alive
long enough

53:15.670 --> 53:17.759
to find another food source.

53:17.803 --> 53:19.761
♪

53:19.805 --> 53:21.676
You mean us?

53:21.720 --> 53:23.330
♪

53:23.374 --> 53:25.550
At the rate it's growing,

53:25.593 --> 53:29.380
it would need
a warm-blooded food source.

53:29.423 --> 53:32.513
Not the easiest thing to find
in the middle of the ocean.

53:32.557 --> 53:34.602
Dana...

53:34.646 --> 53:36.691
are you believing any of this?

53:36.735 --> 53:37.866
♪

53:37.910 --> 53:41.392
The... the thing you saw...

53:41.435 --> 53:43.568
you can show us, right?

53:43.611 --> 53:44.830
♪

53:44.873 --> 53:46.397
It's dead.

53:46.440 --> 53:48.268
It's gone.
Of course it is.

53:48.312 --> 53:50.401
It... it crawled out
of the man's mouth,

53:50.444 --> 53:52.533
and then it just...

53:52.577 --> 53:53.708
I-I don't know, it...

53:53.752 --> 53:55.884
it just melted.

53:55.928 --> 53:58.583
So whatever it was,
it's dead now, right?

53:58.626 --> 54:00.628
So there's nothing
to worry about.

54:00.672 --> 54:02.717
[Breathing heavily]
Right?

54:02.761 --> 54:05.285
What was inside
that man's body...

54:05.329 --> 54:06.591
♪

54:06.634 --> 54:09.637
It was too small to have made
the bite marks.

54:09.681 --> 54:11.291
♪

54:11.335 --> 54:12.597
[door crashes]

54:12.640 --> 54:14.599
[all breathing heavily]
Kat and Rusty,

54:14.642 --> 54:16.340
they weren't in
the engine room.

54:16.383 --> 54:18.385
Rusty? Kat?

54:18.429 --> 54:19.821
Is that you?

54:19.865 --> 54:22.868
[Knocking against door]

54:22.911 --> 54:25.740
♪

54:25.784 --> 54:29.527
[sinister music]

54:29.570 --> 54:31.746
- Jesus.
- [whimpers]

54:31.790 --> 54:34.880
[all breathing heavily]

54:34.923 --> 54:36.403
Get...

54:36.447 --> 54:37.839
it...

54:37.883 --> 54:39.711
off.

54:39.754 --> 54:43.845
♪

54:43.889 --> 54:45.412
[gasps]

54:45.456 --> 54:48.589
♪

54:48.633 --> 54:50.939
[creature squelching]

54:50.983 --> 54:53.594
We... we have to get it off
of her!

54:53.638 --> 54:55.466
- Don't touch it!
- [shouts]

54:55.509 --> 54:58.425
♪

54:58.469 --> 55:00.688
[both gasp, yelp]

55:00.732 --> 55:02.429
Don't let it get away!

55:02.473 --> 55:04.779
[Creature clanging in pipe]

55:04.823 --> 55:07.391
[thunder crashing]

55:07.434 --> 55:10.394
[suspenseful music]

55:10.437 --> 55:12.831
♪

55:14.441 --> 55:17.966
[foreboding music]

55:18.010 --> 55:20.404
We can seal it with this.

55:20.447 --> 55:24.930
♪

55:24.973 --> 55:27.759
[ship groaning]

55:27.802 --> 55:29.761
♪

55:29.804 --> 55:32.764
[tape crackling]

55:32.807 --> 55:34.505
Michelle?

55:34.548 --> 55:35.810
How's she doing?

55:35.854 --> 55:37.638
She's breathing.

55:37.682 --> 55:40.467
But I have no idea
what kind of internal damage

55:40.511 --> 55:42.426
it may have done.
What if it put

55:42.469 --> 55:44.732
one of those things
inside of her...

55:44.776 --> 55:46.778
like you found on that man?

55:46.821 --> 55:49.781
♪

55:49.824 --> 55:51.478
I don't know.

55:51.522 --> 55:54.438
Could be what's
keeping her alive.

55:54.481 --> 55:56.527
I've got something.

55:56.570 --> 55:58.833
[Grunts]

55:58.877 --> 56:01.488
[wind howling]
[ship creaking]

56:01.532 --> 56:06.493
♪

56:06.537 --> 56:08.016
Okay, um...

56:08.060 --> 56:09.757
the last call he made

56:09.801 --> 56:11.629
was four days ago.

56:11.672 --> 56:14.632
The coordinates
were put in here.

56:14.675 --> 56:17.461
That's right in the middle
of the Mariana Trench.

56:17.504 --> 56:19.854
What the hell
was he doing there?

56:19.898 --> 56:21.508
The Mariana Trench?

56:21.552 --> 56:23.597
The world's deepest part
of the ocean.

56:23.641 --> 56:25.033
36,000 feet down.

56:25.077 --> 56:27.514
You could sink
Mount Everest in there

56:27.558 --> 56:30.952
and the peak would still be
a good mile underwater.

56:30.996 --> 56:34.521
- Uh, I-I recovered fragments
of a video

56:34.565 --> 56:37.568
that he tried to upload
from his phone.

56:37.611 --> 56:44.575
♪

56:44.618 --> 56:47.708
Are... are those core samples?

56:47.752 --> 56:49.449
They can't be.

56:49.493 --> 56:51.625
The trench
is a protected monument.

56:51.669 --> 56:52.800
♪

56:52.844 --> 56:55.716
- Wait, s-stop there.

56:55.760 --> 56:57.588
Go back a little.

56:57.631 --> 56:59.067
Stop.

56:59.111 --> 57:01.896
Tamor Oil and Gas.

57:01.940 --> 57:04.638
Son of a bitch.

57:04.682 --> 57:05.900
What is it?

57:05.944 --> 57:08.990
They're looking for oil.

57:09.034 --> 57:11.558
But that's illegal.

57:11.602 --> 57:13.081
Some genius
in the U.S. government

57:13.125 --> 57:15.780
has been talking about allowing
drilling in the trench.

57:15.823 --> 57:17.738
Looks like these guys
were secretly trying

57:17.782 --> 57:20.088
to get a jump-start
on the competition.

57:20.132 --> 57:22.526
Okay, that still doesn't
explain what happened

57:22.569 --> 57:24.615
to that man.
Or how he ended up

57:24.658 --> 57:26.660
in the ocean
200 miles from there.

57:26.704 --> 57:29.097
No one's ever dug that deep.

57:29.141 --> 57:31.578
And there sure as hell isn't
any warm-blooded food source

57:31.622 --> 57:34.581
anywhere near that depth
it could have fed on.

57:34.625 --> 57:37.105
They're messing
with the unknown down there.

57:37.149 --> 57:39.847
Who knows what kind
of microbe they brought up?

57:39.891 --> 57:42.067
Something desperate
to live.

57:42.110 --> 57:43.938
That's for sure.

57:43.982 --> 57:45.026
[Muffled crash]

57:45.070 --> 57:47.594
[all groan]

57:47.638 --> 57:48.943
[ship groaning]

57:48.987 --> 57:51.772
[all groaning,
breathing heavily]

57:51.816 --> 57:54.601
Uh, I downloaded this

57:54.645 --> 57:56.124
off my camera.

57:56.168 --> 58:00.128
[Tense music]

58:00.172 --> 58:02.870
Watch the side of his neck.

58:02.914 --> 58:07.614
♪

58:07.658 --> 58:08.659
[amazed exclamation]

58:08.702 --> 58:11.139
Whatever it is, it's...

58:11.183 --> 58:12.967
it's a lot bigger now.

58:13.011 --> 58:14.621
♪

58:14.665 --> 58:16.797
If we see that thing again,

58:16.841 --> 58:20.627
we need to stay away
from the smaller tentacles.

58:20.671 --> 58:23.630
I think it uses them
like a jellyfish

58:23.674 --> 58:25.893
to render its victim
unconscious.

58:25.937 --> 58:27.808
♪

58:27.852 --> 58:30.594
That's probably why you don't
remember being attacked.

58:30.637 --> 58:31.682
♪

58:31.725 --> 58:33.161
That's a nice thought.

58:33.205 --> 58:34.859
[All yelp]

58:34.902 --> 58:36.774
[ship groaning]

58:36.817 --> 58:38.645
[wind whistling]

58:38.689 --> 58:40.604
[gasping]

58:40.647 --> 58:42.997
♪

58:43.041 --> 58:45.609
This is useless
without the engine.

58:45.652 --> 58:48.002
The ocean's just
throwing us around now.

58:48.046 --> 58:50.831
[Panting]

58:50.875 --> 58:53.007
We need to find Kat.

58:53.051 --> 58:56.620
Find out how close they were
to getting the engine going.

58:56.663 --> 58:59.100
We can't just ride out
the storm in here?

58:59.144 --> 59:02.190
If we can't turn the bow
into the waves, we're...

59:02.234 --> 59:05.019
we're eventually gonna capsize.

59:05.063 --> 59:07.718
But there's a chance
we won't, right?

59:07.761 --> 59:09.763
A chance we'll make it through.

59:09.807 --> 59:12.592
All it will take
is one rogue wave,

59:12.636 --> 59:14.812
and that wave will come.

59:14.855 --> 59:18.032
But for all we know,
Kat could be dead already.

59:18.076 --> 59:20.034
Food for that...

59:20.078 --> 59:22.733
thing out there.
We all better hope

59:22.776 --> 59:25.126
that Kat is alive, because...

59:25.170 --> 59:28.173
without Rusty,
she's our only shot.

59:28.216 --> 59:30.175
Look, you all do
what you want,

59:30.218 --> 59:32.046
but I'm not going, all right?

59:32.090 --> 59:35.223
I'll... I'll stay here
and look after Rusty.

59:35.267 --> 59:37.225
[All scream]

59:37.269 --> 59:39.706
[waves crashing]

59:39.750 --> 59:41.665
[metal clanging]

59:41.708 --> 59:43.188
♪

59:43.231 --> 59:45.886
There's nothing more
you can do for Rusty.

59:45.930 --> 59:48.149
We need you with us...

59:48.193 --> 59:50.717
in case Kat is injured.

59:52.110 --> 59:54.025
I'm sorry.

59:54.068 --> 59:57.071
I'm not... I'm just not going.

59:57.115 --> 59:59.857
All right?

59:59.900 --> 01:00:02.076
If we do nothing,

01:00:02.120 --> 01:00:04.862
we're all dead for sure.

01:00:04.905 --> 01:00:09.823
♪

01:00:09.867 --> 01:00:12.260
I'll go.

01:00:12.304 --> 01:00:15.176
We don't have much
of a choice here.

01:00:15.220 --> 01:00:17.788
We got to face
our fears, right?

01:00:17.831 --> 01:00:23.097
♪

01:00:23.141 --> 01:00:26.100
[dramatic music]

01:00:26.144 --> 01:00:32.803
♪

01:00:32.846 --> 01:00:34.805
[wind whistling]

01:00:34.848 --> 01:00:36.894
[thunder crashing]

01:00:36.937 --> 01:00:42.769
♪

01:00:42.813 --> 01:00:45.816
[rain pattering]
[wind whistling]

01:00:47.948 --> 01:00:50.081
The flares are in
the lifeboat locker.

01:00:50.124 --> 01:00:51.952
Come on.

01:00:51.996 --> 01:00:53.954
[Wind whistling]

01:00:53.998 --> 01:00:56.783
[thunder rumbling]

01:01:03.007 --> 01:01:04.791
Um, we should probably get

01:01:04.835 --> 01:01:07.011
some supplies
from the sick bay, right?

01:01:07.054 --> 01:01:09.840
Just in case.

01:01:09.883 --> 01:01:12.886
[Thunder rumbling]

01:01:12.930 --> 01:01:15.889
[suspenseful music]

01:01:15.933 --> 01:01:22.896
♪

01:01:22.940 --> 01:01:24.158
You know how to use
one of these?

01:01:24.202 --> 01:01:26.160
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:01:26.204 --> 01:01:27.335
Okay.

01:01:27.379 --> 01:01:29.990
♪

01:01:30.034 --> 01:01:31.905
It's locked.

01:01:31.949 --> 01:01:36.780
♪

01:01:36.823 --> 01:01:38.085
[loud bang]
[both scream]

01:01:38.129 --> 01:01:40.871
- Is everything all right?
- All good!

01:01:40.914 --> 01:01:43.351
[Thunder rumbling]

01:01:43.395 --> 01:01:50.707
♪

01:01:52.883 --> 01:01:55.842
[ship creaking]

01:01:55.886 --> 01:02:00.194
♪

01:02:00.238 --> 01:02:03.197
[breathing heavily]

01:02:03.241 --> 01:02:10.248
♪

01:02:13.077 --> 01:02:14.339
Kat?

01:02:14.382 --> 01:02:16.907
[Hollow clanging]

01:02:16.950 --> 01:02:19.300
♪

01:02:19.344 --> 01:02:21.346
Kat?

01:02:21.389 --> 01:02:26.220
[Ship groaning, creaking]

01:02:26.264 --> 01:02:27.352
Michelle.

01:02:27.395 --> 01:02:29.397
Come on.
I'm sorry.

01:02:29.441 --> 01:02:31.138
I-I just can't.

01:02:31.182 --> 01:02:33.227
[Whimpering]
Michelle!

01:02:33.271 --> 01:02:34.402
[Metallic bang]

01:02:34.446 --> 01:02:37.405
What's going on?

01:02:37.449 --> 01:02:39.843
You guys go!
I'll meet you at sick bay!

01:02:39.886 --> 01:02:41.409
- What are you doing?
- I'm getting Michelle!

01:02:41.453 --> 01:02:43.368
Go!
Dana!

01:02:43.411 --> 01:02:46.937
[Thunder rumbling]

01:02:46.980 --> 01:02:48.852
[gasps]

01:02:48.895 --> 01:02:50.897
♪

01:02:50.941 --> 01:02:53.900
[breathing heavily]

01:02:53.944 --> 01:02:55.119
♪

01:02:55.162 --> 01:02:57.121
Michelle!

01:02:57.164 --> 01:03:00.167
[Yelps]
Come on, Michelle!

01:03:00.211 --> 01:03:01.255
♪

01:03:01.299 --> 01:03:04.258
[sinister music]

01:03:04.302 --> 01:03:06.217
♪

01:03:06.260 --> 01:03:08.959
[screams]

01:03:09.002 --> 01:03:10.874
♪

01:03:10.917 --> 01:03:13.093
[screams]

01:03:13.137 --> 01:03:14.921
Get it off!
[yelps]

01:03:14.965 --> 01:03:16.140
[both screaming]

01:03:16.183 --> 01:03:17.358
♪

01:03:17.402 --> 01:03:19.186
Get it off me!
No!

01:03:19.230 --> 01:03:21.188
[Screaming continues]

01:03:21.232 --> 01:03:24.104
- Michelle!
- [screaming]

01:03:24.148 --> 01:03:26.280
Get it off!
Michelle!

01:03:26.324 --> 01:03:29.240
Michelle!
[shrieking]

01:03:29.283 --> 01:03:30.937
[screams]
Michelle!

01:03:30.981 --> 01:03:32.983
[Flesh squelches]

01:03:33.026 --> 01:03:35.986
[tense music]

01:03:36.029 --> 01:03:38.466
♪

01:03:38.510 --> 01:03:41.818
[coughing, gasping]

01:03:43.210 --> 01:03:46.126
Hell of a way to go.

01:03:46.170 --> 01:03:48.999
- I got the morphine.
- Good.

01:03:49.042 --> 01:03:50.478
We need to go!
We need to get

01:03:50.522 --> 01:03:53.090
to the engine room now!
Dana?

01:03:53.133 --> 01:03:56.093
[Foreboding music]

01:03:56.136 --> 01:03:57.311
♪

01:03:57.355 --> 01:03:59.052
We need to find Kat.

01:03:59.096 --> 01:04:01.054
We need to get
to the engine room... now!

01:04:01.098 --> 01:04:03.056
Where... where's Michelle?

01:04:03.100 --> 01:04:04.362
[Panting]

01:04:04.405 --> 01:04:07.234
She... she's dead.

01:04:07.278 --> 01:04:09.106
Dead?

01:04:09.149 --> 01:04:11.369
How?
I don't...

01:04:11.412 --> 01:04:12.936
♪

01:04:12.979 --> 01:04:14.024
[ship groans]

01:04:14.067 --> 01:04:15.155
[all shouting]

01:04:15.199 --> 01:04:17.897
[metal creaking]

01:04:17.941 --> 01:04:21.161
[all breathing heavily]

01:04:21.205 --> 01:04:22.902
Move!
What are you doing?

01:04:22.946 --> 01:04:23.903
- Move!
- [screams]

01:04:23.947 --> 01:04:25.905
[gunshots]

01:04:25.949 --> 01:04:27.341
♪

01:04:27.385 --> 01:04:29.387
[whimpering]

01:04:29.430 --> 01:04:31.345
[gasps]

01:04:31.389 --> 01:04:34.174
[sinister music]

01:04:34.218 --> 01:04:35.436
What?

01:04:35.480 --> 01:04:42.226
♪

01:04:42.269 --> 01:04:44.489
Go!
Get out of here! Go!

01:04:44.532 --> 01:04:46.447
[Whimpers]

01:04:46.491 --> 01:04:49.233
[gunshots]

01:04:49.276 --> 01:04:50.495
[gun clicking]

01:04:50.538 --> 01:04:52.366
Dana!

01:04:52.410 --> 01:04:58.024
♪

01:04:58.068 --> 01:05:00.026
[grunts]

01:05:00.070 --> 01:05:01.419
[all panting]

01:05:01.462 --> 01:05:03.421
[ship groaning]

01:05:03.464 --> 01:05:05.945
[straining]

01:05:05.989 --> 01:05:07.947
[hollers]
The hinges are rusted!

01:05:07.991 --> 01:05:09.514
I'll give you a hand.

01:05:09.557 --> 01:05:12.517
I know I left this open.

01:05:12.560 --> 01:05:15.172
[Gasps]
It's jammed or something.

01:05:15.215 --> 01:05:17.391
Just pull!
[both straining]

01:05:17.435 --> 01:05:19.959
The engine room door
won't open!

01:05:20.003 --> 01:05:22.527
- We'll be right there.
- [straining]

01:05:22.570 --> 01:05:24.964
[all grunting]

01:05:25.008 --> 01:05:26.400
[both panting]

01:05:26.444 --> 01:05:28.054
We're in!
We're in!

01:05:28.098 --> 01:05:29.969
[Screams]

01:05:30.013 --> 01:05:32.189
- No!
- You live through this,

01:05:32.232 --> 01:05:34.452
you hear me?
No!

01:05:34.495 --> 01:05:36.454
No! No!

01:05:36.497 --> 01:05:38.151
[Screaming]
Dana!

01:05:38.195 --> 01:05:40.284
Dana, you are not dying
because of me.

01:05:40.327 --> 01:05:42.068
Now go!

01:05:42.112 --> 01:05:45.071
[Gagging]
No!

01:05:45.115 --> 01:05:47.291
No! No! No!

01:05:47.334 --> 01:05:49.162
[Sobbing]
Dana, Dana, Dana.

01:05:49.206 --> 01:05:51.121
No, we can't just leave her!

01:05:51.164 --> 01:05:52.296
No!

01:05:52.339 --> 01:05:54.428
Get away from the door... now.

01:05:54.472 --> 01:06:00.478
♪

01:06:00.521 --> 01:06:02.088
It was you.

01:06:02.132 --> 01:06:03.611
You...

01:06:03.655 --> 01:06:06.527
you were holding down
the latches.

01:06:06.571 --> 01:06:09.008
You were trying
to keep us out.

01:06:09.052 --> 01:06:11.228
Get away from the door... now.

01:06:11.271 --> 01:06:13.230
You are not letting that thing
back in here.

01:06:13.273 --> 01:06:15.319
Do you hear me?

01:06:15.362 --> 01:06:18.322
[Tense music]

01:06:18.365 --> 01:06:20.628
[metallic clang]

01:06:20.672 --> 01:06:21.629
[waves crashing]

01:06:21.673 --> 01:06:24.632
[ship groaning]

01:06:24.676 --> 01:06:29.072
♪

01:06:29.115 --> 01:06:31.074
Coward.

01:06:31.117 --> 01:06:33.554
Better than being
a dead hero.

01:06:33.598 --> 01:06:35.469
[Ship groans]

01:06:35.513 --> 01:06:38.298
[grunts]
[screams]

01:06:38.342 --> 01:06:40.039
- [grunts]
- Dana!

01:06:40.083 --> 01:06:42.389
Stop it!
[screaming]

01:06:42.433 --> 01:06:44.478
Stop, Kat. Stop!

01:06:44.522 --> 01:06:46.480
- [Grunts]
- Stop it!

01:06:46.524 --> 01:06:48.134
♪

01:06:48.178 --> 01:06:49.396
Stop it!

01:06:49.440 --> 01:06:51.355
Stop, all right?

01:06:51.398 --> 01:06:52.660
Dana!

01:06:52.704 --> 01:06:54.488
- [Screaming]
- [grunts]

01:06:54.532 --> 01:06:56.142
Dana!

01:06:56.186 --> 01:06:58.101
Get off her, Dana!

01:06:58.144 --> 01:07:00.668
- [Whimpering]
- Stop it, you guys!

01:07:00.712 --> 01:07:02.192
Stop!
Just stop!

01:07:02.235 --> 01:07:05.369
All right, stop!
[gasping, panting]

01:07:05.412 --> 01:07:07.153
It's bad enough we need
to worry about

01:07:07.197 --> 01:07:08.546
that thing out there.

01:07:08.589 --> 01:07:10.635
Now we need to worry
about each other?

01:07:10.678 --> 01:07:13.507
[All panting]
Why?

01:07:13.551 --> 01:07:15.205
♪

01:07:15.248 --> 01:07:18.077
Why?
Why would you do that?

01:07:18.121 --> 01:07:20.558
Don't you dare judge me.

01:07:20.601 --> 01:07:24.127
♪

01:07:24.170 --> 01:07:26.390
[gasping, panting]

01:07:26.433 --> 01:07:28.087
♪

01:07:28.131 --> 01:07:30.133
You have no idea
what I've lived through

01:07:30.176 --> 01:07:33.179
down here just to get
this thing fixed.

01:07:33.223 --> 01:07:35.529
I wasn't about to let it all
be for nothing.

01:07:35.573 --> 01:07:42.232
♪

01:07:42.275 --> 01:07:45.235
You've been working on this
the entire time?

01:07:45.278 --> 01:07:47.454
♪

01:07:47.498 --> 01:07:51.110
Rusty and I just...
just started working on it

01:07:51.154 --> 01:07:53.286
when I heard her scream.

01:07:53.330 --> 01:07:55.201
I went looking for her.

01:07:55.245 --> 01:07:58.204
Next thing I know, I'm
waking up behind the gearbox.

01:07:58.248 --> 01:07:59.553
♪

01:07:59.597 --> 01:08:02.687
Rusty, she... she's next to me.

01:08:02.730 --> 01:08:05.211
That thing is already on her.

01:08:05.255 --> 01:08:07.648
Feeding on her or something.

01:08:07.692 --> 01:08:10.434
When you came in to...
to check the generator...

01:08:10.477 --> 01:08:11.696
♪

01:08:11.739 --> 01:08:14.481
I wanted to say something,
you know?

01:08:14.525 --> 01:08:16.179
♪

01:08:16.221 --> 01:08:18.354
Cry out for help.

01:08:18.398 --> 01:08:20.357
But I was so worried that...

01:08:20.399 --> 01:08:23.273
[exhales heavily]
That thing would turn on me.

01:08:23.316 --> 01:08:25.578
♪

01:08:25.622 --> 01:08:28.147
Rusty...

01:08:28.191 --> 01:08:30.497
she managed to get back
on her feet,

01:08:30.541 --> 01:08:33.238
if you can believe it.

01:08:33.283 --> 01:08:35.154
[Inhales deeply]
She followed you

01:08:35.198 --> 01:08:37.243
right out of here.

01:08:37.287 --> 01:08:38.243
[Sighs]

01:08:38.287 --> 01:08:40.377
[sniffles]

01:08:40.420 --> 01:08:43.728
She was always stronger
than me.

01:08:43.770 --> 01:08:46.600
So you waited for her
to leave and...

01:08:46.644 --> 01:08:48.602
you locked yourself in?

01:08:48.645 --> 01:08:51.649
You're damn right I did.

01:08:51.692 --> 01:08:55.479
And any one of you would have
done exactly the same thing.

01:08:55.522 --> 01:08:58.698
You said the engine is fixed.

01:08:58.743 --> 01:09:00.658
Close.
[sighs]

01:09:00.701 --> 01:09:03.356
I just need to reroute
the fuel line.

01:09:03.399 --> 01:09:05.402
That's great.

01:09:05.444 --> 01:09:06.620
We're gonna get out of here.

01:09:06.663 --> 01:09:09.319
We're gonna get through this.

01:09:09.362 --> 01:09:10.755
There's a catch.

01:09:10.798 --> 01:09:13.497
It'll need to be started
from the bridge.

01:09:13.540 --> 01:09:15.629
The electrical
is shot to hell down here.

01:09:15.673 --> 01:09:17.413
I had to bypass it.

01:09:17.457 --> 01:09:21.679
♪

01:09:21.721 --> 01:09:24.638
How long do you need?

01:09:24.682 --> 01:09:26.684
With an extra set of hands,

01:09:26.727 --> 01:09:29.513
15, 20 minutes, tops.

01:09:29.555 --> 01:09:34.518
♪

01:09:34.560 --> 01:09:37.216
I'll do it.

01:09:37.260 --> 01:09:40.350
I'll start it from the bridge.

01:09:40.393 --> 01:09:42.830
But first...

01:09:42.874 --> 01:09:46.225
what do you think is gonna
kill that thing?

01:09:46.269 --> 01:09:48.227
Electricity.

01:09:48.270 --> 01:09:50.229
♪

01:09:50.273 --> 01:09:52.231
It might do the trick.

01:09:52.274 --> 01:09:55.234
[Dramatic music]

01:09:55.278 --> 01:09:58.455
♪

01:09:58.498 --> 01:09:59.717
Kat?

01:09:59.760 --> 01:10:01.545
Where is it?
It's in the cabinet

01:10:01.588 --> 01:10:04.287
with the wrenches.
I've got some wire.

01:10:04.330 --> 01:10:07.290
[Suspenseful music]

01:10:07.333 --> 01:10:09.509
♪

01:10:09.553 --> 01:10:11.381
Bingo.

01:10:11.424 --> 01:10:13.731
♪

01:10:13.774 --> 01:10:16.560
All right.

01:10:16.603 --> 01:10:19.432
♪

01:10:19.476 --> 01:10:21.565
This'll work?

01:10:21.608 --> 01:10:23.349
Oh, it'll work.

01:10:23.393 --> 01:10:25.482
Whether it'll kill that thing
is a different question.

01:10:25.525 --> 01:10:27.527
♪

01:10:27.571 --> 01:10:28.876
You won't be able to fire it,

01:10:28.920 --> 01:10:31.575
so you'll need
to get close enough to stab it.

01:10:31.618 --> 01:10:33.707
Don't turn it on till
right before you need it,

01:10:33.751 --> 01:10:35.753
or you'll drain the unit.

01:10:35.796 --> 01:10:38.712
[Sighs]
And obviously, once it's on...

01:10:38.756 --> 01:10:40.497
♪

01:10:40.540 --> 01:10:42.542
Clear.

01:10:42.586 --> 01:10:47.504
♪

01:10:47.547 --> 01:10:48.722
[electricity zapping]

01:10:48.766 --> 01:10:50.724
♪

01:10:50.768 --> 01:10:53.727
You'll want to make sure
you don't touch the spear.

01:10:53.771 --> 01:10:55.381
Okay.

01:10:55.425 --> 01:10:57.731
Ten minutes.
We'll be ready.

01:10:57.775 --> 01:10:58.863
Don't you worry about us.

01:10:58.906 --> 01:11:01.300
You guys just get
to the bridge.

01:11:01.344 --> 01:11:04.390
♪

01:11:05.652 --> 01:11:08.655
[suspenseful music]

01:11:08.699 --> 01:11:12.790
♪

01:11:12.833 --> 01:11:15.488
[ship creaking]

01:11:15.532 --> 01:11:22.539
♪

01:11:26.717 --> 01:11:30.416
[both breathing shakily]

01:11:30.460 --> 01:11:37.467
♪

01:12:07.453 --> 01:12:08.889
[sinister music]

01:12:08.933 --> 01:12:10.543
Gwenn!

01:12:10.587 --> 01:12:11.805
- Dana, wait!
- Gwenn!

01:12:11.849 --> 01:12:13.372
Gwenn!
Wait!

01:12:13.416 --> 01:12:14.808
[Waves crashing]

01:12:14.852 --> 01:12:16.375
[ship creaking]

01:12:16.419 --> 01:12:18.595
[yelps]
Gwenn!

01:12:18.638 --> 01:12:20.379
Dana!

01:12:20.423 --> 01:12:22.642
Dana, wait!

01:12:22.686 --> 01:12:24.514
[Grunts]

01:12:24.557 --> 01:12:26.690
[exclaims]

01:12:26.733 --> 01:12:28.866
Wait up!
[yelps]

01:12:28.909 --> 01:12:30.607
♪

01:12:30.650 --> 01:12:31.912
Gwenn!

01:12:31.956 --> 01:12:33.436
She's heading for the bridge!

01:12:33.479 --> 01:12:35.568
Come on!

01:12:35.612 --> 01:12:37.875
[Both yelp]

01:12:37.918 --> 01:12:39.659
[suspenseful music]

01:12:39.703 --> 01:12:41.705
- Dana!
- [coughing]

01:12:41.748 --> 01:12:44.490
- Are you all right?
- [gasping]

01:12:44.534 --> 01:12:45.839
I'm fine.

01:12:45.883 --> 01:12:47.754
Gwenn!

01:12:47.798 --> 01:12:49.843
She's alive!
She's headed to the bridge!

01:12:49.887 --> 01:12:52.846
[Panting]

01:12:52.890 --> 01:12:59.897
♪

01:13:00.550 --> 01:13:04.858
[door creaking]

01:13:04.902 --> 01:13:06.773
- [yelps]
- [panting]

01:13:06.817 --> 01:13:08.906
[thunder rumbling]

01:13:08.949 --> 01:13:11.430
[both panting]

01:13:11.474 --> 01:13:13.519
[stammering]

01:13:13.563 --> 01:13:16.957
- Oof!
- Gwenn?

01:13:17.001 --> 01:13:19.525
♪

01:13:19.569 --> 01:13:21.440
Gwenn?

01:13:21.484 --> 01:13:23.877
[Ship groans, creaks]

01:13:23.921 --> 01:13:26.532
♪

01:13:26.576 --> 01:13:28.665
Gwenn?

01:13:28.708 --> 01:13:31.755
♪

01:13:31.798 --> 01:13:34.540
[eerie creaking]

01:13:34.584 --> 01:13:37.630
♪

01:13:37.674 --> 01:13:40.024
Gwenn, are you in here?

01:13:40.067 --> 01:13:44.898
♪

01:13:44.942 --> 01:13:47.597
Gwenn?

01:13:47.640 --> 01:13:49.555
Gwenn!

01:13:49.599 --> 01:13:51.775
[Waves crashing]

01:13:51.818 --> 01:13:58.825
♪

01:14:01.524 --> 01:14:03.917
[gasps softly]
Hang in there.

01:14:03.961 --> 01:14:05.789
Okay.

01:14:05.832 --> 01:14:07.486
[Hollering indistinctly]

01:14:07.530 --> 01:14:09.053
[shudders]

01:14:09.096 --> 01:14:11.098
♪

01:14:11.142 --> 01:14:13.666
We need to get
the engine started.

01:14:13.710 --> 01:14:16.060
Make sure the bow thrusters
are engaged.

01:14:16.103 --> 01:14:17.627
[Grunts]

01:14:17.670 --> 01:14:20.499
♪

01:14:20.543 --> 01:14:23.589
[grunting]

01:14:23.633 --> 01:14:24.721
♪

01:14:24.764 --> 01:14:25.765
[buttons clicking]

01:14:25.809 --> 01:14:27.506
[grunts]

01:14:27.550 --> 01:14:29.726
Good to go.

01:14:29.769 --> 01:14:31.989
Come on, Kat.

01:14:32.032 --> 01:14:34.644
♪

01:14:34.687 --> 01:14:36.602
Come on.

01:14:36.646 --> 01:14:37.821
[Sobs]

01:14:37.864 --> 01:14:39.692
Call the engine room
and find out

01:14:39.736 --> 01:14:41.738
what the hell is going on!
[whimpers]

01:14:41.781 --> 01:14:43.522
[ship creaking]

01:14:43.566 --> 01:14:45.611
[grunts, yelps]

01:14:45.655 --> 01:14:47.526
♪

01:14:47.570 --> 01:14:50.747
[waves crashing]

01:14:50.790 --> 01:14:52.096
Sparks!

01:14:52.139 --> 01:14:54.098
Sparks!

01:14:54.141 --> 01:14:55.665
♪

01:14:55.708 --> 01:14:56.970
[grunting]

01:14:57.014 --> 01:14:58.668
Come on.

01:14:58.711 --> 01:15:00.800
Start, you son of a bitch!

01:15:00.844 --> 01:15:02.628
[Sobbing]

01:15:02.672 --> 01:15:04.761
[engines humming]

01:15:04.804 --> 01:15:06.850
[triumphant music]

01:15:06.893 --> 01:15:08.678
[laughs]

01:15:08.721 --> 01:15:10.984
Yes! Yes!

01:15:11.028 --> 01:15:12.769
We did it!

01:15:12.812 --> 01:15:14.988
We did it, Sparks!

01:15:15.032 --> 01:15:17.556
[Engines powering up]

01:15:17.600 --> 01:15:19.645
I'll be right there.

01:15:19.689 --> 01:15:20.864
I'm just gonna...

01:15:20.907 --> 01:15:23.649
set the autopilot.

01:15:23.693 --> 01:15:25.172
I'm coming, okay?

01:15:25.216 --> 01:15:26.870
We're going home.

01:15:26.913 --> 01:15:29.829
[Screams]

01:15:29.873 --> 01:15:31.657
[sinister music]

01:15:31.701 --> 01:15:33.877
[coughing, gasping]

01:15:33.920 --> 01:15:36.749
♪

01:15:36.793 --> 01:15:38.751
Let me...
[choking]

01:15:38.795 --> 01:15:40.927
[gasping]

01:15:40.971 --> 01:15:43.103
Gwenn, no.

01:15:43.147 --> 01:15:44.801
♪

01:15:44.844 --> 01:15:47.586
[weeping]
It...

01:15:47.630 --> 01:15:49.719
must...

01:15:49.762 --> 01:15:50.937
die.

01:15:50.981 --> 01:15:54.027
[Sobbing]

01:15:54.071 --> 01:15:56.029
[screams]

01:15:56.073 --> 01:15:57.857
- N-no!

01:15:57.901 --> 01:16:00.164
No!
[wheezing]

01:16:00.207 --> 01:16:02.949
♪

01:16:02.993 --> 01:16:05.038
No!

01:16:05.082 --> 01:16:07.693
[Sobbing]

01:16:09.173 --> 01:16:10.740
Gwenn!

01:16:10.783 --> 01:16:12.611
[Screams]

01:16:12.655 --> 01:16:14.831
[electricity crackling]

01:16:14.874 --> 01:16:16.659
[sobbing]

01:16:16.702 --> 01:16:18.051
[gasping]

01:16:18.095 --> 01:16:25.102
♪

01:16:26.190 --> 01:16:28.932
She did... did it.

01:16:28.975 --> 01:16:30.629
She saved us.

01:16:32.065 --> 01:16:33.937
Sparks?

01:16:33.980 --> 01:16:35.721
What did you do?

01:16:35.765 --> 01:16:37.070
♪

01:16:37.114 --> 01:16:39.769
Sparks!
Help, Dana!

01:16:39.812 --> 01:16:41.074
Help me!
Sparks!

01:16:41.118 --> 01:16:43.642
- Get it off!
- Sparks!

01:16:43.686 --> 01:16:46.079
Help me!
[gasping]

01:16:46.123 --> 01:16:48.081
[screams]
Get it off!

01:16:48.125 --> 01:16:50.910
[Sobbing]
[yelps]

01:16:50.954 --> 01:16:54.697
♪

01:16:54.740 --> 01:16:56.873
[sobbing]

01:16:56.916 --> 01:16:58.918
♪

01:16:58.962 --> 01:17:00.833
[creature splatters]

01:17:00.877 --> 01:17:03.836
[both gasping]

01:17:03.880 --> 01:17:05.708
[tense music]

01:17:05.751 --> 01:17:07.971
- What are you doing?
- Killing this son of a bitch

01:17:08.014 --> 01:17:09.886
once and for all.
No!

01:17:09.929 --> 01:17:12.236
Just let the storm take it!
It's gonna die

01:17:12.279 --> 01:17:14.238
here and now!
We don't even know

01:17:14.281 --> 01:17:16.196
if it's gonna work!
[sobbing]

01:17:16.240 --> 01:17:18.764
[exclaiming]

01:17:18.808 --> 01:17:20.766
♪

01:17:20.810 --> 01:17:22.855
[gasping]

01:17:22.899 --> 01:17:24.117
[yelps]

01:17:24.161 --> 01:17:26.772
- [hollers]
- [screaming]

01:17:26.816 --> 01:17:27.991
Sparks!

01:17:28.034 --> 01:17:30.689
- No, no!
- Sparks!

01:17:30.733 --> 01:17:33.692
No! Sparks!
[screaming]

01:17:33.736 --> 01:17:34.780
Go!

01:17:34.824 --> 01:17:36.826
Get out of here!

01:17:36.869 --> 01:17:39.002
- No!
- [screaming]

01:17:39.045 --> 01:17:41.700
- No!
- [screams]

01:17:41.744 --> 01:17:43.963
Sparks!

01:17:44.007 --> 01:17:49.926
♪

01:17:49.969 --> 01:17:52.929
[panting]

01:17:52.972 --> 01:17:55.714
♪

01:17:55.758 --> 01:17:58.717
[sinister music]

01:17:58.761 --> 01:18:00.806
♪

01:18:00.850 --> 01:18:02.808
[gasps, whimpers]

01:18:04.375 --> 01:18:06.246
Is this it?

01:18:06.290 --> 01:18:08.771
It'll do.

01:18:08.814 --> 01:18:09.902
[Ship creaking]

01:18:09.946 --> 01:18:11.948
[hatch clanks]

01:18:11.991 --> 01:18:13.166
Dana?

01:18:13.210 --> 01:18:15.168
Is that you?

01:18:15.212 --> 01:18:16.996
[Suspenseful music]

01:18:17.040 --> 01:18:19.259
[breathing heavily]

01:18:19.303 --> 01:18:23.002
♪

01:18:23.046 --> 01:18:25.048
Where is Sparks?

01:18:25.091 --> 01:18:29.879
♪

01:18:29.922 --> 01:18:32.055
Gwenn too.

01:18:32.098 --> 01:18:35.319
♪

01:18:35.362 --> 01:18:38.191
I'm so sorry.

01:18:38.235 --> 01:18:40.193
Were you able to set
the autopilot?

01:18:40.237 --> 01:18:42.195
♪

01:18:42.239 --> 01:18:44.067
Yeah, I...

01:18:44.110 --> 01:18:47.200
I set it for Guam.

01:18:47.244 --> 01:18:50.073
- [laughs]
- But, um...

01:18:50.116 --> 01:18:52.945
we can't let that happen.

01:18:52.989 --> 01:18:54.817
♪

01:18:54.860 --> 01:18:56.949
We can't let what happen?

01:18:56.993 --> 01:18:58.211
[Ship creaks]

01:18:58.255 --> 01:19:00.213
[yelps]

01:19:00.257 --> 01:19:02.172
♪

01:19:02.215 --> 01:19:04.391
There's no killing
that thing out there.

01:19:04.435 --> 01:19:06.350
♪

01:19:06.393 --> 01:19:08.831
That man tried
to destroy the engine.

01:19:08.874 --> 01:19:11.355
He... he knew
what he was doing.

01:19:11.398 --> 01:19:13.096
♪

01:19:13.139 --> 01:19:15.228
He was trying to...

01:19:15.272 --> 01:19:17.056
stop that thing
from spreading.

01:19:17.100 --> 01:19:19.102
He was trying to stop...

01:19:19.145 --> 01:19:21.104
stop it from getting
to anyone else.

01:19:21.147 --> 01:19:24.020
♪

01:19:24.063 --> 01:19:25.804
You're not suggesting
that we...

01:19:25.848 --> 01:19:28.894
That we let the ship sink.

01:19:28.938 --> 01:19:32.245
With that thing and us on it.

01:19:32.289 --> 01:19:33.986
That's crazy.

01:19:34.030 --> 01:19:35.118
That's suicide.

01:19:35.161 --> 01:19:36.249
Tell her.

01:19:36.293 --> 01:19:39.122
Tell her it's crazy.

01:19:39.165 --> 01:19:42.125
You've seen what that thing
is capable of.

01:19:42.168 --> 01:19:45.911
♪

01:19:45.955 --> 01:19:47.913
Do we really want to be
the ones responsible

01:19:47.957 --> 01:19:50.916
for unleashing that
onto the rest of the world?

01:19:50.960 --> 01:19:52.265
Our friends?

01:19:52.309 --> 01:19:54.137
Our families?

01:19:54.180 --> 01:19:56.008
Who says it's not gonna find
something else

01:19:56.052 --> 01:19:57.140
to feed on out there?

01:19:57.183 --> 01:19:58.924
Whales, seals.

01:19:58.968 --> 01:20:00.883
They're warm-blooded, right?

01:20:00.926 --> 01:20:03.059
We would have died for nothing.
There's a greater chance

01:20:03.102 --> 01:20:05.888
it'll starve and die
if it goes down with us.

01:20:05.931 --> 01:20:07.150
[Ship creaking]

01:20:07.193 --> 01:20:10.327
Listen, all I know is,
I'm going home.

01:20:10.370 --> 01:20:12.329
I have a life, plans,

01:20:12.372 --> 01:20:14.157
and I'm sure as hell
not dying out here

01:20:14.200 --> 01:20:16.899
in the middle
of the goddamn ocean.

01:20:16.942 --> 01:20:18.944
Just because you have
no one left does not mean

01:20:18.988 --> 01:20:21.164
you can sacrifice
the rest of us.

01:20:21.207 --> 01:20:22.295
♪

01:20:22.339 --> 01:20:25.864
I'm sorry, Kat.

01:20:25.908 --> 01:20:27.866
I really am,
but we have to do this.

01:20:27.910 --> 01:20:28.954
[Waves crashing]

01:20:28.998 --> 01:20:30.869
[all groan]

01:20:30.913 --> 01:20:32.871
[ship creaking]

01:20:32.915 --> 01:20:35.439
♪

01:20:35.482 --> 01:20:37.180
- No!
- Wait, no!

01:20:37.223 --> 01:20:38.442
- Kat.
- Let it go!

01:20:38.485 --> 01:20:40.487
[All shouting]

01:20:40.531 --> 01:20:43.186
- Stop it!
- I'm not dying here!

01:20:43.229 --> 01:20:45.884
Stop it!
[all yelp]

01:20:45.928 --> 01:20:48.191
[choking]

01:20:48.234 --> 01:20:50.410
[screams]
Kat!

01:20:50.454 --> 01:20:53.065
- Don't make me do this.
- [yelps]

01:20:53.109 --> 01:20:56.068
[both struggling]

01:20:56.112 --> 01:21:00.116
♪

01:21:00.159 --> 01:21:03.119
[both shouting, grunting]

01:21:03.162 --> 01:21:07.471
♪

01:21:07.514 --> 01:21:10.213
[both cry out]

01:21:10.256 --> 01:21:14.217
♪

01:21:14.260 --> 01:21:16.306
- [grunts]
- [yelps]

01:21:16.349 --> 01:21:18.395
[choking, gasping]

01:21:18.438 --> 01:21:20.353
There has to be
another option.

